- Me - A name I call myself

676
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:09,760
-Far -是一段漫漫長路
- Far - A long long way to run

677
01:01:10,003 --> 01:01:13,370
-Sew -是用針拉著線
- Sew - A needle pulling thread

678
01:01:13,673 --> 01:01:16,938
-La -是Sew之後的音
- La - A note to follow sew

679
01:01:17,144 --> 01:01:20,136
-Tea -是配果醬麵包的飲品
- Tea - A drink with jam and bread

680
01:01:20,347 --> 01:01:24,215
那樣我們又回到Doe
That will bring us back to doe

681
01:01:41,802 --> 01:01:48,071
當你學會音符後
When you know the notes to sing

682
01:01:48,642 --> 01:01:55,138
你幾乎可以唱任何歌
You can sing most anything

683
01:01:55,715 --> 01:01:58,878
Doe是一頭雌性的鹿
Doe A deer, a female deer

684
01:01:59,152 --> 01:02:02,679
Ray是一線金色的陽光
Ray A drop of golden sun

685
01:02:02,889 --> 01:02:06,347
Me是我對自己的稱呼
Me A name I call myself

686
01:02:06,593 --> 01:02:09,756
Far是一段漫漫長路
Far A long long way to run

687
01:02:10,030 --> 01:02:13,193
Sew是用針拉著線
Sew A needle pulling thread

688
01:02:13,400 --> 01:02:16,597
La是Sew之後的音
La A note to follow sew

689
01:02:17,204 --> 01:02:19,832
Tea是配果醬麵包的飲品
Tea A drink with jam and bread

690
01:02:20,073 --> 01:02:24,032
那樣我們又回到…
That will bring us back to

691
01:02:24,244 --> 01:02:31,082
So do la fa mi do re
So-do-la-fa-mi-do-re

692
01:02:31,351 --> 01:02:35,845
So do la fa ti
So-do-la-fa-ti

693
01:02:36,089 --> 01:02:37,716
La so
La-so

694
01:02:41,261 --> 01:02:47,063
Ti do
Ti-do

695
01:02:47,267 --> 01:02:48,757
So do
So-do

696
01:03:02,215 --> 01:03:05,309
這些山真是壯觀 真是棒透了
The mountains are magnificent, really magnificent.

697
01:03:05,552 --> 01:03:08,214
-我特別為你而升起的 -哦？
- I had them put up just for you. - Oh?

698
01:03:08,488 --> 01:03:10,649
萬尺高山
Even if it's to a height of 10,000 feet...

699
01:03:10,924 --> 01:03:14,451
蓋爾總是相信 它的升起是為了特殊場合
...Georg always believes in "rising to the occasion."

700
01:03:14,728 --> 01:03:16,992
你的笑話不改進的話 我就要收回邀請了
Improve the jokes or I'll disinvite you.

701
01:03:17,597 --> 01:03:20,157
你並未邀請我 我是不請自來的
You didn't invite me. I invited myself.

702
01:03:20,433 --> 01:03:22,958
-當然 -你需要伴護人
- Naturally. - You needed a chaperone...

703
01:03:23,236 --> 01:03:25,966
我需要有佳餚…
...and I needed a place where the cuisine is superb...

704
01:03:26,239 --> 01:03:28,833
美酒的地方
...the wine cellar unexcelled...

705
01:03:29,142 --> 01:03:31,736
而價格又公道
...and the price perfect.

706
01:03:32,112 --> 01:03:33,943
麥斯，你真的太過分了
Max, you are outrageous.

707
01:03:34,180 --> 01:03:38,173
一點也不，我是很迷人的食客
Not at all. I'm a very charming sponge.

708
01:03:40,820 --> 01:03:41,946
聽
Listen.

709
01:03:44,291 --> 01:03:46,521
那是可普曼修道院的唱詩班
That's the Klopmann Monastery Choir.

710
01:03:49,529 --> 01:03:51,156
他們唱得很好
They're good.

711
01:03:52,198 --> 01:03:53,825
非常好
Very good.

712
01:03:54,634 --> 01:03:57,296
以後幾天裡我要探索這地區
I must explore this area in the next few days.

713
01:03:57,504 --> 01:04:00,962
在某處，有個渴望被發掘的 合唱團在等我發掘
Somewhere, a hungry singing group is waiting for Max Detweiler...

714
01:04:01,207 --> 01:04:05,507
並在薩爾斯堡的音樂節時 一舉成名
...to pluck it out and make it famous at the Salzburg Folk Festival.

715
01:04:05,712 --> 01:04:09,011
-他們有名而你就有利 -那不公平，我得承認
- They get fame, you get money. - It's unfair, I admit it.

716
01:04:09,282 --> 01:04:13,651
但有天一切都會改變 我也會成名的
But someday that'll be changed. I shall get the fame too.

717
01:04:20,694 --> 01:04:22,855
天啊，這是怎麼回事？
Good heavens, what's this?

718
01:04:24,297 --> 01:04:26,629
沒什麼，只是本地的頑童
It's nothing. Just some local urchins.

719
01:04:41,848 --> 01:04:45,750
在這裡和你在一起 真的讓我很興奮
This really is exciting for me, Georg. Being here with you.

720
01:04:46,586 --> 01:04:49,146
樹林，湖澤 這些你都已經看過了
Trees, lakes, you've seen them before.

721
01:04:49,422 --> 01:04:52,016
我不是這個意思 你是知道的
That is not what I mean, and you know it.

722
01:04:52,258 --> 01:04:56,217
-你是指我嗎？我令你興奮？ -不可能嗎？
- You mean me? I'm exciting? - Is that so impossible?

723
01:04:56,496 --> 01:04:59,522
不是，只是不會發生
No, just highly improbable.

724
01:04:59,766 --> 01:05:03,930
-又來了，又看低自己了 -我是危險的駕駛人
- There you go, running yourself down. - Well, I'm a dangerous driver.

725
01:05:07,707 --> 01:05:11,404
在這裡，我好像比較 容易瞭解你，蓋爾
You're much less of a riddle when I see you here, Georg.

726
01:05:11,611 --> 01:05:14,444
-在我生長的地方？ -是的，正是
- In my natural habitat? - Yes, exactly.

727
01:05:14,748 --> 01:05:16,875
你是說在這
Are you saying that I'm more at home...

728
01:05:17,117 --> 01:05:21,110
鳥語花香的地方
...among the birds and the flowers and the wind that moves...

729
01:05:21,388 --> 01:05:23,549
我感覺較舒適？
...through the trees like a restless sea?

730
01:05:23,790 --> 01:05:25,382
多有詩意啊
How poetic.

731
01:05:25,592 --> 01:05:27,457
是的，我是的，不是嗎？
Yes, it was rather, wasn't it?

732
01:05:28,595 --> 01:05:33,726
我覺得在此比在維也納安逸 在你們那奢華的沙龍裡
More at home here than in Vienna in all your glittering salons...

733
01:05:33,933 --> 01:05:38,302
和那些無聊漢附庸風雅喝香檳
...gossiping gaily with bores I detest, soaking myself in champagne...

734
01:05:38,605 --> 01:05:42,302
被那不知名的華爾滋所牽絆
...stumbling about to waltzes by Strausses I can't even remember?

735
01:05:42,609 --> 01:05:44,736
-你就是想告訴我這些嗎？ -是的
- Is that what you're saying? - Yes.

736
01:05:44,978 --> 01:05:47,276
你為何會有那概念？
Now whatever gave you that idea?

737
01:05:50,650 --> 01:05:54,552
我真的喜歡這兒，蓋爾 如此可愛和寧靜
Oh, I do like it here, Georg. It's so lovely and peaceful.

738
01:05:54,888 --> 01:05:56,822
你怎捨得經常離開此地？
How can you leave it so often?

739
01:05:57,090 --> 01:05:59,923
我想是假裝自己還是很活躍
Oh, pretending to be madly active, I suppose.

740
01:06:00,160 --> 01:06:03,425
活躍使生命看似充滿了目的
Activity suggests a life filled with purpose.

741
01:06:04,164 --> 01:06:06,428
可能是在逃避回憶
Could it be running away from memories?

742
01:06:09,636 --> 01:06:13,572
也許是在尋求留下的理由
Or perhaps just searching for a reason to stay.

743
01:06:14,240 --> 01:06:17,732
我希望那是你 常去維也納的理由
I hope that's why you've been coming to Vienna so often.

744
01:06:18,411 --> 01:06:22,745
-還是那兒有讓你著魔的事物？ -我不能說是你令我著魔的
- Were there other distractions? - I'd hardly call you a distraction.

745
01:06:22,982 --> 01:06:25,644
那你如何形容我，蓋爾？
Well, what would you call me, Georg?

746
01:06:27,921 --> 01:06:29,183
漂亮…
Lovely...

747
01:06:30,190 --> 01:06:32,818
美麗，聰明有風度 很完美的女主人
...charming, witty, graceful, the perfect hostess...

748
01:06:33,026 --> 01:06:35,859
你會恨我這樣說的：
...and, you're going to hate me for this...

749
01:06:36,296 --> 01:06:38,355
有點像是我的救世主
...in a way, my savior.

750
01:06:38,631 --> 01:06:40,462
真不浪漫呀
Oh, how unromantic.

751
01:06:40,667 --> 01:06:42,999
如果我不告訴你 那我就是不知感恩的小人了
I'd be an ungrateful wretch if I didn't say...

752
01:06:43,269 --> 01:06:46,500
是你使我重新體會生命的意義
...that you brought some meaning back into my life.

753
01:06:48,341 --> 01:06:51,105
我想我是受寵若驚
I am amusing, I suppose.

754
01:06:51,344 --> 01:06:56,111
我擁有維也納最好的地方 最上流的社交圈子的朋友
I have the finest couturier in Vienna and a glittering circle of friends.

755
01:06:56,316 --> 01:06:59,444
-和舉辦最豪華的派對 -是的
- I do give some rather gay parties. - Oh, yes.

756
01:06:59,686 --> 01:07:01,517
除去那些…
But take all that away...

757
01:07:01,721 --> 01:07:06,158
我只是一個富有 和飄浮不定的人
...and you have just wealthy, unattached little me...

758
01:07:06,826 --> 01:07:09,226
在尋尋覓覓，就像你一樣
...searching, just like you.

759
01:07:14,334 --> 01:07:16,029
多來點餡餅嗎？
More strudel, Herr Detweiler?

760
01:07:16,302 --> 01:07:17,826
-我吃了多少？ -兩個了
- How many have I had? - Two.

761
01:07:18,071 --> 01:07:20,005
那麼它就成為第三個吧
Make it an uneven three.

762
01:07:23,309 --> 01:07:26,335
還在吃，麥斯？ 一定是不太快樂
Still eating, Max? Must be unhappy.

763
01:07:26,546 --> 01:07:30,505
數月來我一直想從何洛克那邊 弄來那隊四重奏
That mixed quartet I've been trying to steal away from Sol Hurok...

764
01:07:30,750 --> 01:07:33,412
-發生何事？ -沙夏皮特搶先了
- What happened? ...Sascha Petrie stole them first.

765
01:07:33,653 --> 01:07:34,915
我最恨賊了
I hate thieves.

766
01:07:35,188 --> 01:07:38,487
麥斯，你要學習自愛
Max, you really must try and learn to love yourself.

767
01:07:38,725 --> 01:07:41,057
為此事我得打長途電話到巴黎 羅馬及斯德哥爾摩
I had to call Paris, Rome and Stockholm.

768
01:07:41,327 --> 01:07:44,888
-當然是用蓋爾的電話了 -要不然我怎麼負擔得起？
- On Georg's telephone, of course. - How else could I afford it?

769
01:07:45,365 --> 01:07:50,496
我喜歡有錢人，我喜歡他們的 生活方式，尤其和他們一起生活時
I like rich people, the way they live and how I live when I'm with them.

770
01:07:50,837 --> 01:07:52,828
我在想孩子們上哪兒去了
I wonder where the children are.

771
01:07:53,239 --> 01:07:55,730
他們一定是聽見我來 躲起來了
They must have heard I was coming and hid.

772
01:07:56,009 --> 01:07:58,500
我是希望他們會在家歡迎你的
I was hoping they'd be here to welcome you.

773
01:07:58,745 --> 01:08:03,239
麥斯，試著放開朗一些，好嗎？
Max, do step out of character for a moment and try and be charming.

774
01:08:12,292 --> 01:08:13,691
怎樣？
Well?

775
01:08:14,594 --> 01:08:15,788
什麼怎樣？
Well what?

776
01:08:16,029 --> 01:08:18,930
你讓蓋爾決定了沒？ 我是否會聽見婚禮鐘聲？
Have you made up his mind? Do I hear wedding bells?

777
01:08:19,199 --> 01:08:21,190
-很有希望 -太棒了
- Pealing madly. - Marvelous.

778
01:08:21,434 --> 01:08:24,198
-但不一定跟我有關 -那是什麼意思？
- Not necessarily for me. - What kind of talk's that?

779
01:08:24,404 --> 01:08:25,962
那跟你無關
None-of-your-business talk.

780
01:08:26,272 --> 01:08:28,706
我很喜歡蓋爾 我不准你把我們當玩具
I'm terribly fond of him, so don't toy with us.

781
01:08:28,975 --> 01:08:32,570
但我是個孩子，我喜歡玩具 所以告訴我一切吧
But I'm a child. I like toys. So tell me everything.

782
01:08:32,879 --> 01:08:37,942
快點，告訴麥斯一切的細節
Come on. Tell me every teensy-weensy, intimate, disgusting detail.

783
01:08:39,419 --> 01:08:43,549
我有感覺，我來這裡的目的 是要得到認可
Well, let's just say I have a feeling I may be here on approval.

784
01:08:43,790 --> 01:08:46,816
-我同意了，你怎會錯過？ -很容易的
- I approve of that. How can you miss? - Far too easily.

785
01:08:47,093 --> 01:08:50,324
如我瞭解你的話 我知道你會找到方法的
If I know you, darling, and I do, you will find a way.

786
01:08:50,597 --> 01:08:53,088
-他不是普通人 -他很富有
- He's no ordinary man. - No, he's rich.

787
01:08:53,333 --> 01:08:55,597
他老婆的死 給他帶來可怕的心痛
His wife's death gave him a great heartache.

788
01:08:55,802 --> 01:08:58,930
當你先生死時 他留給你一筆可觀的遺產
And your husband's death gave you a great fortune.

789
01:08:59,138 --> 01:09:01,106
麥斯，你真是怪物
Oh, Max, you really are a beast.

790
01:09:01,307 --> 01:09:05,334
你和蓋爾對我來講，就像是一家人 所以我想看到你們兩人結婚
You and Georg are like family. That's why I want to see you married.

791
01:09:05,578 --> 01:09:09,139
我們必須保留那筆錢 在同一家庭中
We must keep all that lovely money in the family.

792
01:09:25,431 --> 01:09:28,366
-你在幹什麼？ -范艦長
- What are you doing there? - Oh, Captain von Trapp.

793
01:09:28,635 --> 01:09:30,660
我正在找…
I was just looking for...

794
01:09:31,537 --> 01:09:34,370
我沒看到，我不知道你…
I didn't see, I mean, I didn't know you were...

795
01:09:34,974 --> 01:09:36,669
希特勒萬歲
Heil Hitler!

796
01:09:37,377 --> 01:09:38,867
你是誰？
Who are you?

797
01:09:39,145 --> 01:09:41,375
我送電報給德維勒先生
I have a telegram for Herr Detweiler.

798
01:09:41,648 --> 01:09:44,378
-我就是 -是的，先生
- I am Herr Detweiler. - Yes, sir.

799
01:09:49,455 --> 01:09:52,049
好，電報你送到了，滾吧
You've delivered your telegram. Now get out.

800
01:09:58,831 --> 01:10:02,232
-蓋爾，他只是個小男孩 -是，而我只是個奧地利人
- Georg, he's just a boy. - Yes, and I'm just an Austrian.

801
01:10:02,468 --> 01:10:05,232
要發生的遲早會發生 只要確定不會發生在你身上
Things will happen. Make sure they don't happen to you.

802
01:10:05,538 --> 01:10:08,200
麥斯，你別再這樣說
Max! Don't you ever say that again.

803
01:10:08,474 --> 01:10:10,669
你知道我沒有政治主張
I have no political convictions.

804
01:10:10,910 --> 01:10:13,845
-人人都如此時我可以怎樣？ -有東西可以做的
- Can I help it if other people do? - You can help it.

805
01:10:14,981 --> 01:10:17,142
一定有
You must help it.

806
01:10:27,427 --> 01:10:29,019
哈囉
Hello?

807
01:10:31,664 --> 01:10:34,428
你如此遙遠，你在哪兒？
You're far away. Where are you?

808
01:10:34,734 --> 01:10:38,602
在一個遙不可及的世界裡
In a world that's disappearing, I'm afraid.

809
01:10:39,439 --> 01:10:43,034
我有辦法帶你回到現實世界嗎？
Is there any way I could bring you back to the world I'm in?

810
01:11:08,968 --> 01:11:11,459
-爸爸，是爸爸！ -是你們爸爸！
- Father! Father! - There's your father!

811
01:11:12,271 --> 01:11:14,899
哦，艦長，你回來了
Oh, captain, you're home!

812
01:11:23,282 --> 01:11:25,944
立刻從水裡上來
Come out of that water at once!

813
01:11:35,061 --> 01:11:37,256
你一定是史蕾特男爵夫人
Oh, you must be Baroness Schraeder.

814
01:11:42,568 --> 01:11:45,560
我濕透了！
I'm soaked to the skin!

815
01:11:57,517 --> 01:11:58,916
排好
Straight line!

816
01:12:13,599 --> 01:12:15,999
這位是史蕾特男爵夫人
This is Baroness Schraeder.

817
01:12:18,604 --> 01:12:20,367
而這些…
And these...

818
01:12:20,606 --> 01:12:22,198
是我的孩子們
...are my children.

819
01:12:23,309 --> 01:12:24,799
你們好
How do you do?

820
01:12:25,878 --> 01:12:30,611
進去屋裡，抹幹身子，清潔好 換衣服後再回來此地
Go inside, dry off, clean up, change your clothes and report back here!

821
01:12:35,621 --> 01:12:37,714
小姐，請你留下來
Fraulein, you will stay here, please!

822
01:12:39,459 --> 01:12:43,020
我最好去看麥斯在幹什麼
I think I'd better go see what Max is up to.

823
01:12:53,239 --> 01:12:55,002
小姐…
Now, fraulein...

824
01:12:56,909 --> 01:12:58,968
我要你據實回答
...I want a truthful answer.

825
01:12:59,378 --> 01:13:00,845
是的，艦長
Yes, captain.

826
01:13:01,147 --> 01:13:05,208
是真有可能，或只是我的想像…
Is it possible, or could I have just imagined it?

827
01:13:06,719 --> 01:13:11,213
我的孩子們今天有爬過樹？
Have my children, by any chance, been climbing trees today?

828
01:13:11,691 --> 01:13:12,851
是的，艦長
Yes, captain.

829
01:13:13,926 --> 01:13:15,257
這樣
I see.

830
01:13:15,828 --> 01:13:20,322
我能否請教他們哪來的這些
And where, may I ask, did they get these...

831
01:13:20,600 --> 01:13:22,659
-遊戲服 -你是如此稱呼它們的
- Play clothes. - Is that what they are?

832
01:13:22,869 --> 01:13:26,270
是我拿我臥房裡的 舊窗簾所做的
I made them from the drapes that used to hang in my bedroom.

833
01:13:27,073 --> 01:13:29,200
-窗簾？ -還剩下很多
- Drapes? - They have plenty of wear left.

834
01:13:29,408 --> 01:13:31,342
孩子們穿著玩了不少地方
We've been everywhere in them.

835
01:13:31,577 --> 01:13:36,037
你是在告訴我 我的孩子穿著舊窗簾的布料…
Are you telling me that my children have been roaming about Salzburg...

836
01:13:36,249 --> 01:13:39,616
玩遍了薩爾斯堡？
...dressed up in nothing but some old drapes?

837
01:13:39,852 --> 01:13:41,513
而且玩得很開心
And having a marvelous time!

838
01:13:41,721 --> 01:13:44,952
-他們有制服 -對不起那是瘋子穿的
- They have uniforms. - Forgive me, straitjackets.

839
01:13:45,191 --> 01:13:47,955
孩子們不該擔心他們會弄髒 他們珍貴的制服
They can't be children if they worry about clothes...

840
01:13:48,227 --> 01:13:49,353
我沒聽過埋怨
They don't complain.

841
01:13:49,595 --> 01:13:52,291
