1010
01:27:54,539 --> 01:27:56,097
晚安，父親
Good night, Father.

1011
01:27:59,077 --> 01:28:00,908
晚安，麥斯伯伯
Good night, Uncle Max.

1012
01:28:02,814 --> 01:28:05,977
那將會是我的第一次舞會，父親
It'll be my first party, Father!

1013
01:28:38,517 --> 01:28:41,145
-艦長 -你好，吉勒先生，男爵夫人
- Captain. - Herr Zeller. Baroness Schraeder.

1014
01:28:41,353 --> 01:28:44,481
-你好，吉勒先生 -男爵夫人
- Good evening, Herr Zeller. - Baroness.

1015
01:28:45,791 --> 01:28:48,259
你好
How do you do? Good evening.

1016
01:29:08,880 --> 01:29:12,316
我想你注意到大廳上當眼處 掛著奧地利國旗
Did you notice the obvious display of the Austrian flag?

1017
01:29:19,391 --> 01:29:21,188
女人們看來好漂亮
The women look so beautiful.

1018
01:29:21,460 --> 01:29:22,791
我覺得她們好醜
I think they look ugly.

1019
01:29:23,061 --> 01:29:24,892
你這樣說是因為你怕她們
You're just scared of them.

1020
01:29:25,130 --> 01:29:27,360
傻瓜！只有成人才會怕女人
Silly, only grown-up men fear women.

1021
01:29:27,966 --> 01:29:31,527
-我認為男人看來好美 -你怎麼會知道？
- I think the men look beautiful. - How would you know?

1022
01:29:49,172 --> 01:29:51,197
莉莎，你在跟誰跳舞？
Liesl, who are you dancing with?

1023
01:29:51,408 --> 01:29:53,035
沒有人
Nobody.

1024
01:29:53,844 --> 01:29:55,744
哦，的確沒有
Oh, yes, you are.

1025
01:29:58,215 --> 01:29:59,705
我有這份榮幸嗎？
May I have this dance?

1026
01:29:59,916 --> 01:30:02,407
我很樂意的，年輕人
I'd be delighted, young man.

1027
01:30:09,192 --> 01:30:11,854
你們為何不告訴我 你們會跳舞？
Why didn't you tell me you could dance?

1028
01:30:12,095 --> 01:30:17,032
我們怕你會叫我們一起跳舞 范崔普家庭舞蹈團
We feared you'd make us all dance. The von Trapp Family Dancers.

1029
01:30:21,438 --> 01:30:23,133
他們在演奏什麼？
What are they playing?

1030
01:30:23,373 --> 01:30:26,001
那是奧地利的一種民俗舞曲
It's the Laendler. An Austrian folk dance.

1031
01:30:26,209 --> 01:30:29,372
-教我們 -我很久沒跳過了
- Show me. - I haven't danced since I was little.

1032
01:30:29,579 --> 01:30:31,547
你記得的，求求你
You remember. Please?

1033
01:30:31,815 --> 01:30:33,749
-這個… -拜託嘛
- Well... - Please.

1034
01:30:33,984 --> 01:30:36,214
好吧，過來
All right. Come on over here.

1035
01:30:36,720 --> 01:30:39,553
現在你鞠躬，我答禮
Now you bow and I curtsy.

1036
01:30:40,490 --> 01:30:43,425
-像這樣 -很好，現在我們走幾步！
- Like this? - Fine. Now we go for a little walk.

1037
01:30:43,660 --> 01:30:46,322
1，2，3，1，2，3
One, two, three. One, two, three.

1038
01:30:46,630 --> 01:30:51,226
1，2，3，一起踏步 踏步跳…
One, two, three, step together. Now, step hop, step hop.

1039
01:30:51,468 --> 01:30:54,130
轉圈
Now turn under. Not quite.

1040
01:30:54,337 --> 01:30:58,296
這邊，踏步跳，轉圈
This way. Hop step, hop. And under.

1041
01:30:58,975 --> 01:31:00,670
我們要好好練習呢
Kurt, we'll have to practice.

1042
01:31:00,911 --> 01:31:02,401
讓我來跳好嗎？
Do allow me, will you?

1043
01:32:30,700 --> 01:32:32,565
我不記得了
I don't remember anymore.

1044
01:32:34,738 --> 01:32:36,933
-你的臉好紅 -是嗎？
- Your face is all red. - Is it?

1045
01:32:38,274 --> 01:32:40,367
我想我不習慣跳舞吧
I don't suppose I'm used to dancing.

1046
01:32:43,079 --> 01:32:45,070
那真是跳得太棒了
Why, that was beautifully done.

1047
01:32:45,348 --> 01:32:47,248
你們是迷人的一對
What a lovely couple you make.

1048
01:32:47,450 --> 01:32:49,577
我想孩子們該上床了
It's time the children said good night.

1049
01:32:49,853 --> 01:32:51,184
我們馬上去前廳
We'll be in the hall.

1050
01:32:51,421 --> 01:32:54,288
-我們有特別節目 -是的
- We have something special prepared. - Right!

1051
01:32:54,591 --> 01:32:55,751
是的，快點
Yes, come on!

1052
01:33:02,599 --> 01:33:04,931
蓋爾，你的擔心看來是多餘的
All that needless worrying, Georg.

1053
01:33:05,201 --> 01:33:08,227
你還以為自己在 舞會上找不到朋友
You thought you wouldn't find a friend at the party.

1054
01:33:11,141 --> 01:33:14,736
-今晚外面有點涼，是不是？ -不，我不知道
- A bit chilly out tonight, isn't it? - Oh, I don't know.

1055
01:33:14,944 --> 01:33:16,969
我覺得頗暖和呢！
It seemed rather warm to me.

1056
01:33:21,151 --> 01:33:22,379
先生女士們！
Ladies and gentlemen.

1057
01:33:23,119 --> 01:33:27,215
范崔普艦長的孩子 希望向各位道晚安！
The children of Captain von Trapp wish to say good night to you.

1058
01:33:41,337 --> 01:33:45,239
憂愁的鐘聲來自大廳
There's a sad sort of clanging From the clock in the hall

1059
01:33:45,442 --> 01:33:49,173
塔尖的鐘聲也響起了
And the bells in the steeple too

1060
01:33:49,446 --> 01:33:53,473
在孩子們臥室裡 一隻滑稽的小鳥
And up in the nursery An absurd little bird

1061
01:33:53,683 --> 01:33:56,117
伸出頭來道咕咕
Is popping up to say "coo-coo"

1062
01:33:56,352 --> 01:33:58,013
咕咕
Coo-coo

1063
01:33:58,288 --> 01:33:59,516
咕咕
Coo-coo

1064
01:33:59,756 --> 01:34:01,917
很抱歉他告訴我們
Regretfully they tell us

1065
01:34:02,125 --> 01:34:03,490
要我們向大家
But firmly they compel us

1066
01:34:03,760 --> 01:34:06,820
道晚安
To say goodbye

1067
01:34:07,030 --> 01:34:12,332
向大家
To you

1068
01:34:15,538 --> 01:34:19,440
別了，再見，珍重晚安
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, good night

1069
01:34:19,642 --> 01:34:23,510
我不願離開如斯美景
I hate to go And leave this pretty sight

1070
01:34:30,787 --> 01:34:34,120
別了，再見，珍重再見
So long, farewell, Auf Wiedersehen, adieu

1071
01:34:34,791 --> 01:34:38,318
我向你和你和你說聲再見
Adieu, adieu To you and you and you

1072
01:34:45,668 --> 01:34:49,468
別了，再見，珍重再見
So long, farewell Au revoir, auf Wiedersehen

1073
01:34:49,739 --> 01:34:53,675
我能否留下喝第一口香檳？
I'd like to stay And taste my first champagne

1074
01:34:53,910 --> 01:34:56,344
-可以嗎？ -不行
- Yes? - No.

1075
01:35:00,683 --> 01:35:04,346
別了，再見，珍重再見
So long, farewell Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1076
01:35:04,687 --> 01:35:08,646
我輕歎著離開並說再見
I leave and heave a sigh And say goodbye

1077
01:35:08,858 --> 01:35:12,851
再見
Goodbye

1078
01:35:15,899 --> 01:35:18,993
我真高興可以離去
I'm glad to go

1079
01:35:19,235 --> 01:35:22,102
我不能說謊
I cannot tell a lie

1080
01:35:22,438 --> 01:35:25,430
我展翅，我飄浮
I flit, I float

1081
01:35:25,708 --> 01:35:29,166
我驀地消失，我在飛翔
I fleetly flee, I fly

1082
01:35:39,222 --> 01:35:44,956
太陽已就寢
The sun has gone to bed

1083
01:35:45,195 --> 01:35:48,926
我也一樣
And so must I

1084
01:35:49,132 --> 01:35:51,532
別了
So long

1085
01:35:51,768 --> 01:35:54,328
再見
Farewell

1086
01:35:54,537 --> 01:35:59,941
珍重晚安
Auf Wiedersehen, goodbye

1087
01:36:00,210 --> 01:36:05,546
晚安
Goodbye

1088
01:36:06,249 --> 01:36:11,812
晚安
Goodbye

1089
01:36:12,055 --> 01:36:18,927
晚安
Goodbye

1090
01:36:19,128 --> 01:36:27,627
晚安
Goodbye

1091
01:36:32,642 --> 01:36:35,406
他們真是不同凡響 想想在音樂節的成績
Extraordinary! What they'd do at the festival.

1092
01:36:35,645 --> 01:36:38,136
年輕女士，我必須跟你談談
Young lady, I must have a word with you.

1093
01:36:39,148 --> 01:36:43,141
蓋爾，你不能讓她離去的 她必須參加派對
Georg, you won't let this girl get away. She must join the party.

1094
01:36:43,419 --> 01:36:45,819
-不，我真的… -別說了
- No, really l... - Stop. Stop it now.

1095
01:36:46,089 --> 01:36:49,024
-蓋爾，拜託 -如你願意的話，可以留下來
- Georg, please. - You can if you want to, fraulein.

1096
01:36:49,259 --> 01:36:51,750
我堅持，你會是我今晚的女伴
I insist. You will be my dinner partner.

1097
01:36:51,961 --> 01:36:53,861
這是生意 福蘭斯…
This is business. Franz...

1098
01:36:54,130 --> 01:36:57,293
在我的座位旁 替?莉亞小姐加一個位子
...set another place next to mine for Fraulein Maria.

1099
01:36:59,469 --> 01:37:02,199
-悉聽尊便 -似乎已安排好了
- Whatever you say. - It appears to be all arranged.

1100
01:37:03,006 --> 01:37:04,871
-是的 -我的打扮不適合
- It does. - I'm not suitably dressed.

1101
01:37:05,942 --> 01:37:07,432
你可以換衣服，我們等你
You can change. We'll wait.

1102
01:37:11,047 --> 01:37:13,982
艦長，你一定 很以你的兒女為榮
Captain, you must be very proud of your youngsters.

1103
01:37:14,183 --> 01:37:15,047
是的，謝謝你
I am, thank you.

1104
01:37:15,318 --> 01:37:19,880
還有什麼比孩子們純真的歌聲
Is there a more beautiful expression of what is good in our country...

1105
01:37:20,123 --> 01:37:23,559
更能表現我國的優點？
...than the innocent voices of our children?

1106
01:37:23,960 --> 01:37:25,325
對了，男爵
Oh, come now, baron.

1107
01:37:25,561 --> 01:37:29,327
你想要我們相信 只有奧地利有獨特高尚的品德？
Would you have us believe that Austria holds a monopoly on virtue?

1108
01:37:30,233 --> 01:37:34,363
我們有些人喜歡 悠揚的奧地利歌聲
Herr Zeller, some of us prefer Austrian voices raised in song...

1109
01:37:34,570 --> 01:37:36,970
多於醜陋的德國威脅
...to ugly German threats.

1110
01:37:38,041 --> 01:37:41,670
鴕鳥喜歡埋首于沙中
The ostrich buries his head in the sand...

1111
01:37:41,878 --> 01:37:44,813
有時藏於國旗裡
...and sometimes in the flag.

1112
01:37:45,348 --> 01:37:49,546
或許有些人警告過你合併就要 來臨了，而事實上是的
Perhaps those who would warn you that the Anschluss is coming, and it is...

1113
01:37:49,819 --> 01:37:53,516
或許會以音樂來跟你打交道呢
...would get further with you by setting their words to music.

1114
01:37:53,723 --> 01:37:58,387
如果納粹佔據奧地利 你肯定會是整個小號隊
If the Nazis take over Austria, you will be the entire trumpet section.

1115
01:37:58,695 --> 01:37:59,719
你太恭維我了
You flatter me.

1116
01:38:00,763 --> 01:38:04,665
我真笨拙 我是要指責你的
Oh, how clumsy of me. I meant to accuse you.

1117
01:38:12,408 --> 01:38:14,899
你願意來協助我 真的太仁慈了，男爵夫人
It's very kind of you to offer to help me, baroness.

1118
01:38:15,178 --> 01:38:16,736
我很樂意
I'm delighted, Maria.

1119
01:38:17,213 --> 01:38:20,910
但我實在沒有任何合適的衣服
I really don't think I have anything that would be appropriate.

1120
01:38:21,384 --> 01:38:25,514
那晚你穿的那件迷人衣服呢？
Now where is that lovely little thing you were wearing the other evening?

1121
01:38:25,755 --> 01:38:29,054
使艦長無法將視線從你身上移開
When the captain couldn't keep his eyes off you.

1122
01:38:32,428 --> 01:38:34,259
無法轉移他的目光？
Couldn't keep his eyes off me?

1123
01:38:35,598 --> 01:38:37,395
算了吧，親愛的，我們都是女人
Come, my dear, we are women.

1124
01:38:37,633 --> 01:38:41,034
別再假裝我們不知道 男人在注意我們
Let's not pretend we don't know when a man notices us.

1125
01:38:41,270 --> 01:38:44,706
-找到了 -艦長他注意到每個人
- Here we are. - The captain notices everybody.

1126
01:38:45,274 --> 01:38:47,708
你無需如此抗拒的，?莉亞
There's no need to feel so defensive, Maria.

1127
01:38:47,944 --> 01:38:50,412
你很迷人，你知道嗎？
You are quite attractive, you know.

1128
01:38:50,646 --> 01:38:54,275
如果艦長不注意你的話 他就不是男人了
The captain would hardly be a man if he didn't notice you.

1129
01:38:55,885 --> 01:38:58,251
男爵夫人，我希望你在開玩笑
Baroness, I hope you're joking.

1130
01:38:58,721 --> 01:38:59,983
一點也不
Not at all.

1131
01:39:00,223 --> 01:39:01,815
但我從沒做過任何…
I've never done a thing to...

1132
01:39:02,091 --> 01:39:03,649
你無需如此
You don't have to, my dear.

1133
01:39:04,293 --> 01:39:09,128
對男人而言，沒什麼比 深愛自己的女人更無法抗拒
Nothing's more irresistible to a man than a woman who's in love with him.

1134
01:39:10,400 --> 01:39:12,834
-愛他嗎？ -是的
- In love with him? - Of course.

1135
01:39:13,770 --> 01:39:17,171
最棒的是他也認為自己愛上你了
What makes it so nice is he thinks he's in love with you.

1136
01:39:19,909 --> 01:39:21,501
但那不是事實
But that's not true.

1137
01:39:21,911 --> 01:39:25,403
你當然也注意到 他直視你雙眼時的神情吧
Surely you've noticed the way he looks into your eyes.

1138
01:39:25,681 --> 01:39:30,584
而剛才當他擁著你跳舞時 你臉紅了
And you know, you blushed in his arms when you were dancing just now.

1139
01:39:31,821 --> 01:39:33,516
別太介意
Don't take it to heart.

1140
01:39:33,790 --> 01:39:36,088
他很快就會適應的
He'll get over it soon enough, I think.

1141
01:39:36,359 --> 01:39:38,327
男人都是如此的
Men do, you know.

1142
01:39:39,328 --> 01:39:40,420
那我必須離開了
Then I should go.

1143
01:39:41,764 --> 01:39:43,197
我不能留在此地
I mustn't stay here.

1144
01:39:53,676 --> 01:39:57,112
-我能幫什麼忙嗎？ -沒有
- Is there something I can do to help? - No, nothing.

1145
01:39:58,881 --> 01:40:00,109
有的
Yes.

1146
01:40:01,117 --> 01:40:03,142
求你別告訴艦長這件事
Don't say a word to the captain.

1147
01:40:04,787 --> 01:40:08,348
不，我不會的
No, I wouldn't dream of it.

1148
01:40:15,131 --> 01:40:16,689
再見，?莉亞
Goodbye, Maria.

1149
01:40:17,500 --> 01:40:20,298
我相信你會成為很好的修女
I'm sure you'll make a very fine nun.

1150
01:40:50,333 --> 01:40:52,324
香檳
Champagne, darling.

1151
01:40:52,735 --> 01:40:56,728
我覺得該慶祝一下，乾杯
I feel like celebrating. Cheers.

1152
01:41:02,211 --> 01:41:05,112
-你知道什麼吧 -或許吧
- You know something. - Perhaps.

1153
01:41:05,348 --> 01:41:09,876
若你如此聰明 告訴我如何令?莉亞影響蓋爾
If you're so clever, tell me how to get fraulein to influence Georg.

1154
01:41:10,119 --> 01:41:12,747
我要這些孩子參加音樂節
I want those children in the festival.

1155
01:41:13,222 --> 01:41:15,520
這對奧地利深具意義
Elsa, this is important to Austria.

1156
01:41:15,725 --> 01:41:17,420
對你也不會有妨害的
Wouldn't do you any harm either.

1157
01:41:17,627 --> 01:41:19,219
我曾想過
I thought of that.

1158
01:41:19,462 --> 01:41:21,930
談到影響
Well, if it's a matter of influence...

1159
01:41:22,131 --> 01:41:25,032
你該找我談才對
...maybe the one you have to be talking to is me.

1160
01:44:55,151 --> 01:44:57,381
-2 -3
- Two. - Three.

1161
01:44:57,654 --> 01:44:59,144
-4 -5
- Four. - Five.

1162
01:45:00,423 --> 01:45:02,448
-6 -7
- Six. - Seven.

1163
01:45:02,725 --> 01:45:04,352
Eight.

1164
01:45:04,594 --> 01:45:06,425
-4 -2
- Four. - Two.

1165
01:45:07,530 --> 01:45:09,361
-7 -5
- Seven. - Five.

1166
01:45:09,599 --> 01:45:11,794
-2 -6
- Two. - Six.

1167
01:45:16,439 --> 01:45:18,464
真好玩！
Isn't this fun?

1168
01:45:19,876 --> 01:45:22,208
-4 -我是5號
- Four. - I'm number five.

1169
01:45:22,478 --> 01:45:24,639
-是的 -8
- Oh, yes. - Eight.

1170
01:45:24,948 --> 01:45:27,314
-2 -4
- Two. - Four.

1171
01:45:27,717 --> 01:45:28,945
Six.

1172
01:45:31,421 --> 01:45:32,649
Two.

1173
01:45:33,790 --> 01:45:36,759
男爵夫人，我們累了 不要玩了
Baroness Schraeder, do you mind if we stop now? We're tired.

1174
01:45:36,993 --> 01:45:38,961
隨便你們
Whatever you want, dear.

1175
01:45:39,229 --> 01:45:41,220
明天再玩
We'll do it again tomorrow.

1176
01:45:51,407 --> 01:45:53,568
鄉間真安靜，是不是？
The country's so restful, isn't it?

1177
01:45:54,611 --> 01:45:56,238
喝點檸檬水吧
Have some lemonade.

1178
01:45:57,480 --> 01:45:58,913
一定有更容易的辦法
There must be an easier way.

1179
01:46:00,316 --> 01:46:03,581
想到你做七個孩子的母親 真令我哭笑不得
I get a fiendish delight thinking of you as the mother of seven.

1180
01:46:04,520 --> 01:46:06,351
你計畫如何做呢？
How do you plan to do it?

1181
01:46:06,623 --> 01:46:08,648
你沒聽過
Darling, haven't you ever heard...

1182
01:46:08,925 --> 01:46:12,019
寄宿學校嗎？
...of a delightful little thing called boarding school?

1183
01:46:13,162 --> 01:46:15,426
你真是詭計多端
Baroness Machiavelli.

1184
01:46:16,766 --> 01:46:18,757
麥伯伯，爸爸在哪？
Uncle Max, where's Father?

1185
01:46:19,035 --> 01:46:20,832
我想他在屋子裡
I think he's in the house.

1186
01:46:21,037 --> 01:46:23,597
你們為何都悶悶不樂呢？
What's the matter with all you gloomy pussies?

1187
01:46:23,840 --> 01:46:26,638
-沒什麼 -我知道怎麼辦，我們來做排練
- Nothing. - I know. Let's have a rehearsal.

1188
01:46:26,843 --> 01:46:27,741
為了什麼呢？
What for?

1189
01:46:27,944 --> 01:46:30,435
假裝站在節慶的表演臺上
Let's make believe we're on-stage at the festival.

1190
01:46:30,647 --> 01:46:34,515
-我不想唱 -沒有?莉亞我不想唱
- I don't feel like singing. - Not without Fraulein Maria.

1191
01:46:34,784 --> 01:46:37,184
莉莎去拿吉他，來吧
Liesl, get the guitar. Come on, Marta.

1192
01:46:37,387 --> 01:46:40,356
大家站好，各就各位
Everybody into the group. Get in your places.

1193
01:46:40,623 --> 01:46:43,387
高興點 麗莎，給我們調子
Now be cheerful, right? Give us the key, Liesl.

1194
01:46:45,295 --> 01:46:47,957
現在，開始
Now, impress me.

1195
01:46:51,968 --> 01:46:53,299
葛特兒，你為何不唱呢？
Gretl, why don't you sing?

1196
01:46:53,569 --> 01:46:56,037
我手指痛不能唱
I can't. I've got a sore finger.

1197
01:46:57,073 --> 01:47:00,133
但是你在舞會中唱得很好
But you sang so beautifully the night of the party.

1198
01:47:00,343 --> 01:47:02,675
來，試試看 唱些你們都懂的
Come on, all of you. Try something you know.

1199
01:47:02,912 --> 01:47:04,402
好好享受，快樂些
Enjoy it. Be cheerful.

1200
01:47:04,681 --> 01:47:06,308
好了，莉莎
All right, Liesl.

1201
01:47:08,251 --> 01:47:13,655
群山因為音樂
The hills are alive

1202
01:47:13,890 --> 01:47:21,558
充滿生氣
With the sound of music

1203
01:47:22,765 --> 01:47:27,828
唱了
With songs they have sung

1204
01:47:28,071 --> 01:47:35,910
千年的歌
For a thousand years

1205
01:47:36,612 --> 01:47:42,016
群山讓我的心中
The hills fill my heart

1206
01:47:42,251 --> 01:47:49,953
充滿了音樂
With the sound of music

1207
01:47:50,293 --> 01:47:52,921
他們是唱給我聽
They wanted to sing for me, bless their hearts.

1208
01:47:53,229 --> 01:47:55,129
很好…別停下來
That's lovely, lovely. Don't stop.

1209
01:47:59,135 --> 01:48:03,037
-你喝點飲料吧 -不，謝謝，親愛的
- Something long and cool, Georg? - No, thank you, darling.

1210
01:48:03,439 --> 01:48:05,873
-爸爸 -是的，碧姬塔
- Father? - Yes, Brigitta?

1211
01:48:06,309 --> 01:48:08,573
?莉亞不回來嗎？
Is it true Fraulein Maria isn't coming back?

1212
01:48:08,878 --> 01:48:11,972
是的，我想是不回來了 有什麼好喝嗎？
Yes, I suppose it's true. What have we got here?

1213
01:48:12,281 --> 01:48:16,980
-粉紅檸檬水 -是檸檬水
- Pink lemonade. - Laced with lemonade.

1214
01:48:17,720 --> 01:48:19,244
父親，我不敢相信
I don't believe it, Father.

1215
01:48:20,623 --> 01:48:22,648
-不相信什麼？ -關於?莉亞
- What? - About Fraulein Maria.

1216
01:48:23,059 --> 01:48:24,287
哦，?莉亞
Oh, Fraulein Maria!

1217
01:48:24,594 --> 01:48:28,052
我沒把她的留言告訴你們嗎？ 我肯定我說過了
Didn't I tell you what her note said? I'm sure I did.

1218
01:48:28,798 --> 01:48:31,289
她說她很懷念修道院的生活
She said she missed her life at the abbey.

1219
01:48:31,567 --> 01:48:33,728
她必須離開我們
She had to leave us.

1220
01:48:33,970 --> 01:48:35,562
就這樣
And that's all there is to it.

1221
01:48:37,273 --> 01:48:39,969
好，我現在想嘗點檸檬水
I think I'm brave enough to try some of that.

1222
01:48:40,176 --> 01:48:42,906
-她甚至沒有告別 -她在留言上有說
- She didn't even say goodbye. - She did in her note.

1223
01:48:43,179 --> 01:48:44,976
那是不同的事
That isn't the same thing.

1224
01:48:45,281 --> 01:48:46,908
不甜不酸
Not too sweet, not too sour.

1225
01:48:47,650 --> 01:48:49,641
只是太粉紅了
Just too pink.

1226
01:48:51,087 --> 01:48:54,181
父親，誰是我們的新家庭老師？
Father, who is our new governess going to be?

1227
01:49:00,830 --> 01:49:01,922
這個…
Well...

1228
01:49:04,267 --> 01:49:09,500
你們再也沒有新家庭老師了
...you're not going to have a governess anymore.

1229
01:49:09,839 --> 01:49:12,501
-我們沒有？ -沒有
- We're not? - No.

1230
01:49:14,710 --> 01:49:16,837
你們將要有個新媽媽
You're going to have a new mother.

1231
01:49:17,947 --> 01:49:19,972
一個新媽媽？
A new mother?

1232
01:49:20,817 --> 01:49:23,945
我們昨晚談過了 一切都決定好了
We talked about it last night. It's all settled.

1233
01:49:24,153 --> 01:49:26,849
我們都將會很快樂
And we're all going to be very happy.

1234
01:49:59,856 --> 01:50:02,324
好了…去玩吧
Well, all right, all right. Run off and play.

1235
01:50:34,290 --> 01:50:35,257
是的，孩子們
Yes, my children?

1236
01:50:35,458 --> 01:50:37,858
-我叫莉莎 -怎麼了，麗莎？
- My name is Liesl. - Yes, Liesl?

1237
01:50:38,361 --> 01:50:42,297
我們，我的兄弟姐妹們 要見?莉亞小姐
We, my brothers and sisters, want to see Fraulein Maria.

1238
01:50:43,466 --> 01:50:45,457
?莉亞小姐？
Fraulein Maria?

1239
01:50:46,235 --> 01:50:48,203
哦，?莉亞
Oh, Maria.

1240
01:50:50,106 --> 01:50:51,937
請進來
Come in, please.

1241
01:50:55,811 --> 01:50:57,369
在此等一下
Wait here.

1242
01:51:08,324 --> 01:51:11,487
我是?格麗特修女 我知道你們想見?莉亞
I'm Sister Margaretta. I understand you inquired about Maria.

1243
01:51:11,761 --> 01:51:14,252
我們必須見她 請你告訴她我們在此
We have to see her. Will you tell her we're here?

1244
01:51:14,497 --> 01:51:17,091
-恐怕我做不到 -你一定要告訴她
- I'm afraid I can't do that. - But you've got to!

1245
01:51:17,400 --> 01:51:19,459
-她是我們的家庭教師 -我們要她回來
- She's our governess. - We want her back.

1246
01:51:19,669 --> 01:51:21,569
她甚至沒有道別
She didn't even say goodbye.

1247
01:51:21,804 --> 01:51:23,567
我們想要做的只是和她說話
All we want to do is talk to her.

1248
01:51:24,340 --> 01:51:27,241
我很抱歉，孩子們 但是?莉亞在靜修
I'm very sorry, but Maria is in seclusion.

1249
01:51:27,476 --> 01:51:30,570
-她不願見任何人 -她會見我們的
- She hasn't been seeing anyone. - She'll see us.

1250
01:51:30,813 --> 01:51:33,304
我要讓她看我的手指
I want to show her my finger.

1251
01:51:33,516 --> 01:51:35,416
親愛的，改天吧
Some other time, dear.

1252
01:51:35,685 --> 01:51:36,982
我會告訴她，你們來過
I'll tell her you were here.

1253
01:51:37,253 --> 01:51:40,313
-很高興你們來過 -我們要見?莉亞
- It was sweet of you to call. - We have to speak to her!

1254
01:51:40,957 --> 01:51:44,085
孩子們，回家吧
Run along, children. Run along home.

1255
01:51:44,293 --> 01:51:45,920
我肯定她會見我們
I'm sure she'd like to see us.

1256
01:51:46,195 --> 01:51:48,459
求求你啊
Sister Margaretta, please.

1257
01:51:48,698 --> 01:51:52,429
-再見，孩子們 -求求你啊
- Goodbye, children. - Sister Margaretta, may we, please?

1258
01:51:55,204 --> 01:51:56,933
那是怎麼回事，?格麗特修女？
What was that about, Sister?

1259
01:51:57,173 --> 01:51:59,368
院長，范崔普家的孩子
The von Trapp children, Reverend Mother.

1260
01:51:59,609 --> 01:52:02,043
他們要見?莉亞
They want to see Maria.

1261
01:52:02,311 --> 01:52:04,609
她說了沒？ 她有沒有告訴你什麼事？
Has she spoken yet? Has she told you anything?

1262
01:52:04,880 --> 01:52:08,873
院長，除了祈禱外 她什麼也沒說
She doesn't say a word, Reverend Mother, except in prayer.

1263
01:52:09,151 --> 01:52:10,140
可憐的孩子
Poor child.

1264
01:52:10,353 --> 01:52:13,322
很奇怪，她似乎很高興能回來
It's strange. She seems happy to be back here...

1265
01:52:13,556 --> 01:52:16,855
但同時又很不快樂
...and yet she's unhappy too.

1266
01:52:18,127 --> 01:52:21,187
或許讓她一個人那麼久 是錯誤的
Perhaps I have been wrong in leaving her alone so long.

1267
01:52:21,464 --> 01:52:24,160
我想你最好把她帶來見我 即使她還沒準備好
Bring her to me, even if she's not yet ready.

1268
01:52:24,367 --> 01:52:26,028
是的，院長
Yes, Reverend Mother.

1269
01:52:31,540 --> 01:52:35,032
加絲特修女 帶這位新姐妹到更衣室
Sister Augusta, take our new postulant to the robing room.

1270
01:52:36,045 --> 01:52:38,309
願上帝祝福你，我的女兒
God bless you, my daughter.

1271
01:52:44,520 --> 01:52:46,249
是的，帶她進來
Yes, bring her in.

1272
01:52:55,264 --> 01:52:57,528
你很不快樂，我很難過
You've been unhappy. I'm sorry.

1273
01:52:59,568 --> 01:53:00,762
院長
Reverend Mother.

1274
01:53:01,103 --> 01:53:03,731
他們為何要你回來？
Why did they send you back to us?

1275
01:53:04,573 --> 01:53:06,541
他們沒有要我走 是我主動離開的
They didn't send me back. I left.

1276
01:53:09,045 --> 01:53:10,603
坐下，?莉亞
Sit down, Maria.

1277
01:53:11,113 --> 01:53:12,910
告訴我事情的始末
Tell me what happened.

1278
01:53:18,120 --> 01:53:19,451
是因為我害怕
I was frightened.

1279
01:53:19,722 --> 01:53:24,182
-害怕，是不是他們對你不好？ -哦，不是
- Frightened? Were they unkind to you. - Oh, no!

1280
01:53:24,427 --> 01:53:28,124
我很迷惑，我…
No, I was confused. I felt...

1281
01:53:29,598 --> 01:53:31,691
我從未有那種感覺
I've never felt that way before.

1282
01:53:31,934 --> 01:53:35,700
我不能留下來 我知道遠離他們會比較安全
I couldn't stay. I knew that here I'd be away from it. I'd be safe.

1283
01:53:35,938 --> 01:53:40,637
?莉亞，我們的修道院 不是用來逃避的
Maria, our abbey is not to be used as an escape.

1284
01:53:40,910 --> 01:53:43,140
是什麼事令你無法面對？
What is it you can't face?

1285
01:53:45,114 --> 01:53:46,547
我無法再面對他
I can't face him again.

1286
01:53:47,383 --> 01:53:48,907
他？
Him?

1287
01:53:50,486 --> 01:53:52,545
謝謝你，?格麗特修女
Thank you, Sister Margaretta.

1288
01:54:02,164 --> 01:54:03,791
是范崔普先生？
Captain von Trapp?

1289
01:54:09,238 --> 01:54:11,934
-你是否愛上他了？ -我不知道
- Are you in love with him? - I don't know!

1290
01:54:12,174 --> 01:54:13,641
我不知道…
I don't know. L...

1291
01:54:14,176 --> 01:54:18,010
男爵夫人，她說他愛上我了
The baroness said I was. She said that he was in love with me.

1292
01:54:18,280 --> 01:54:20,942
但我不願相信
But I didn't want to believe it.

1293
01:54:22,017 --> 01:54:24,315
當我們彼此對看時
There were times we looked at each other.

1294
01:54:24,520 --> 01:54:26,078
我簡直不能呼吸
I could hardly breathe.

1295
01:54:26,455 --> 01:54:29,151
-你讓他知道你的感受了嗎？ -我不知道
- Did you let him see your feelings? - I don't know.

1296
01:54:29,759 --> 01:54:32,421
這正是折磨我的原因 我是侍奉神的
That's what's torturing me. I was on God's errand.

1297
01:54:32,628 --> 01:54:37,622
愛他是錯的，我不能留下
To have asked for his love would have been wrong. I just couldn't stay.

1298
01:54:39,802 --> 01:54:42,600
我已作好發誓的準備
I'm ready at this moment to take my vows.

1299
01:54:43,472 --> 01:54:46,532
-請幫助我 -?莉亞
- Please help me. - Maria.

1300
01:54:48,110 --> 01:54:52,809
男女之間的愛也是神聖的 你是可以去愛的
The love of a man and a woman is holy. You have a great capacity to love.

1301
01:54:53,048 --> 01:54:55,983
你必須瞭解 上帝是要你如何去愛
You must find out how God wants you to spend your love.

1302
01:54:56,285 --> 01:55:00,119
但我已獻身上帝 我要終生為上帝服務
But I pledged my life to God. I pledged my life to his service.

1303
01:55:00,322 --> 01:55:04,691
我的女兒，如果你愛這個人 並不表示你就要少愛上帝了
My daughter, if you love this man, it doesn't mean you love God less.

1304
01:55:06,362 --> 01:55:08,227
不
No.

1305
01:55:08,464 --> 01:55:10,329
你必須找出答案
You must find out.

1306
01:55:12,067 --> 01:55:14,558
你必須要回去
You must go back.

1307
01:55:14,837 --> 01:55:16,805
你不能要求我這樣做
You can't ask me to do that.

1308
01:55:17,006 --> 01:55:19,497
-拜託你，讓我留下，我求求你 -?莉亞
- Please let me stay. I beg... - Maria.

1309
01:55:19,708 --> 01:55:23,667
這些牆並不是 建造來逃避問題的
These walls were not built to shut out problems.

1310
01:55:23,879 --> 01:55:25,471
你必須面對它
You have to face them.

1311
01:55:26,048 --> 01:55:29,313
你要過你本來就應過的生活
You have to live the life you were born to live.

1312
01:55:35,191 --> 01:55:39,491
攀登每座山
Climb every mountain

1313
01:55:39,728 --> 01:55:43,494
尋遍高與低
Search high and low

1314
01:55:43,732 --> 01:55:48,499
踏遍每條僻路
Follow every byway

1315
01:55:48,737 --> 01:55:53,003
踏遍每條路
Every path you know

1316
01:55:53,442 --> 01:55:57,902
攀登每座山
Climb every mountain

1317
01:55:58,180 --> 01:56:02,514
涉過每條小溪
Ford every stream

1318
01:56:02,751 --> 01:56:07,120
跟隨每道彩虹
Follow every rainbow

1319
01:56:07,389 --> 01:56:11,723
直至找到你的美夢
Till you find your dream

1320
01:56:11,927 --> 01:56:15,021
這美夢需要你
A dream that will need

1321
01:56:15,264 --> 01:56:20,099
獻出全部的愛
All the love you can give

1322
01:56:20,870 --> 01:56:24,271
在你有生之年
Every day of your life

1323
01:56:24,540 --> 01:56:30,945
一直下去
For as long as you live

1324
01:56:31,247 --> 01:56:35,547
攀登每座山
Climb every mountain

1325
01:56:35,784 --> 01:56:40,118
涉過每條小溪
Ford every stream

1326
01:56:40,389 --> 01:56:44,951
跟隨每道彩虹
Follow every rainbow

1327
01:56:45,160 --> 01:56:53,568
直至找到你的美夢
Till you find your dream

1328
01:56:54,670 --> 01:56:58,162
這美夢需要你
A dream that will need

1329
01:56:58,474 --> 01:57:04,003
獻出全部的愛
All the love you can give

1330
01:57:04,280 --> 01:57:07,772
在你有生之年
Every day of your life

1331
01:57:08,017 --> 01:57:14,445
一直下去
For as long as you live

1332
01:57:14,690 --> 01:57:19,127
攀登每座山
Climb every mountain

1333
01:57:19,361 --> 01:57:23,297
涉過每條小溪
Ford every stream

1334
01:57:23,966 --> 01:57:28,596
跟隨每道彩虹
Follow every rainbow

1335
01:57:29,004 --> 01:57:33,100
直至找到
Till you find...

1336
01:57:33,342 --> 01:57:43,343
你的美夢
...your dream

1337
01:57:45,888 --> 01:57:49,449
這樣神神秘秘的 不像我的孩子
Now, it's not like my children to be secretive.

1338
01:57:49,692 --> 01:57:51,785
我們才不神秘，爸爸
We're not being secretive, Father.

1339
01:57:53,462 --> 01:57:56,795
吃飯遲到也不像我的孩子
And it's not like my children to be late for dinner.

1340
01:57:57,066 --> 01:58:00,502
-我們忘了時間而已 -我知道了
- We lost track of the time. - I see.

1341
01:58:01,303 --> 01:58:04,704
好了，誰要第一個告訴我事實？ 費瑞克
Who's going to be the first one to tell me the truth? Friedrich.

1342
01:58:04,974 --> 01:58:07,033
碧姬塔，莉莎
Brigitta. Liesl.

1343
01:58:08,410 --> 01:58:10,640
你認為我們去哪了？
Where do you think we were, Father?

1344
01:58:17,219 --> 01:58:21,178
如果你不相信我們 你一定是對於我們去哪有點頭緒吧
If you don't believe us, you must have some idea of where you think we were.

1345
01:58:24,760 --> 01:58:26,557
-?塔 -是的，爸爸
- Marta. - Yes, Father.

1346
01:58:26,762 --> 01:58:28,024
你來告訴我
You tell me.

1347
01:58:29,365 --> 01:58:32,994
費瑞克告訴過你，爸爸 我們去采草莓了
Friedrich told you, Father. We were berry picking.

1348
01:58:33,836 --> 01:58:38,500
-我忘了！你們去采草莓 -是呀，我們很喜歡采草莓
- I forgot! You were berry picking. - Yes, we love berry picking.

1349
01:58:38,741 --> 01:58:39,833
整個下午？
All afternoon?

1350
01:58:40,075 --> 01:58:41,804
-是的，我們采了幾千顆 -幾千顆？
- We picked thousands. - Thousands?

1351
01:58:42,011 --> 01:58:44,912
-四處也是呢 -哪一種草莓？
- They were all over the place. - What kind of berries?

1352
01:58:45,180 --> 01:58:48,445
-是藍草莓，先生 -藍草莓
- Blueberries, sir. - Blueberries.

1353
01:58:50,386 --> 01:58:53,753
藍草莓的季節還沒到
It's too early for blueberries.

1354
01:58:55,257 --> 01:58:57,350
-是草莓 -草莓？
- They were strawberries. - Strawberries?

1355
01:58:58,060 --> 01:59:00,756
最近很冷 所以它們變成藍色了
It's been so cold lately, they turned blue.

1356
01:59:06,602 --> 01:59:08,763
很好，讓我看草莓
Very well. Show me the berries.

1357
01:59:10,039 --> 01:59:11,233
-我們… -這個…
- We... - Well...

1358
01:59:11,473 --> 01:59:14,237
-快讓我看草莓 -我們沒有
- Show me the berries you picked. - We don't have them.

1359
01:59:14,476 --> 01:59:16,740
你們沒有？發生了什麼事？
You don't have them? What happened to them?

1360
01:59:16,979 --> 01:59:19,777
-我們… -我們吃了
- We... - We ate them.

1361
01:59:19,982 --> 01:59:22,576
-你們吃了它們？ -是啊
- You ate them? - Yes!

1362
01:59:22,785 --> 01:59:24,377
-它們很好吃 -很好吃
- They were so good. - Delicious.

1363
01:59:24,620 --> 01:59:25,814
非常好
Very well.

1364
01:59:26,088 --> 01:59:31,219
既然你們吃了幾千顆的草莓
Since you've obviously stuffed yourselves on thousands of berries...

1365
01:59:31,460 --> 01:59:35,396
你們不可能肚子餓了 所以我可以告訴思蜜德
...you can't be hungry anymore, so I'll have to tell Frau Schmidt...

1366
01:59:35,631 --> 01:59:38,498
不用煮你們的晚餐
...to skip your dinner.

1367
01:59:47,676 --> 01:59:50,474
都是你的錯 我們應該老實告訴他
It's your fault. We should have told him the truth.

1368
01:59:50,746 --> 01:59:52,714
讓他生我們的氣嗎？
And made him boiling mad at us?

1369
01:59:52,915 --> 01:59:54,849
總比餓死好
It's better than starving to death.

1370
01:59:55,084 --> 01:59:57,951
我們沒有做錯什麼 我們只是想見她
We didn't do anything wrong. We just wanted to see her.

1371
01:59:59,254 --> 02:00:02,348
我的肚子在咕咕叫
My stomach's making noises.

1372
02:00:02,791 --> 02:00:05,624
他們至少可以 讓我們向她打個招呼
The least they could have done was to let us say hello.

1373
02:00:06,762 --> 02:00:10,664
-我們不如吃草吧 -我很不開心
- I wonder what grass tastes like. - I feel awful.

1374
02:00:11,100 --> 02:00:15,366
?莉亞不開心時便會唱那首歌 讓自己心情好轉的
When Fraulein Maria wanted to feel better she used to sing that song.

1375
02:00:15,971 --> 02:00:17,438
我們唱唱看
Let's try it.

1376
02:00:17,673 --> 02:00:20,335
玫瑰上的雨露
Raindrops on roses

1377
02:00:20,642 --> 02:00:24,669
小貓的鬍鬚
And whiskers on kittens

1378
02:00:25,514 --> 02:00:28,108
光亮的銅壺
Bright copper kettles

1379
02:00:28,317 --> 02:00:31,377
溫暖的羊毛手套
And warm woolen mittens

1380
02:00:32,721 --> 02:00:38,682
有細繩的褐色包裝紙
Brown paper packages Tied up with strings

1381
02:00:38,961 --> 02:00:44,957
這些都是我心愛的事物
These are a few of my favorite things

1382
02:00:45,200 --> 02:00:47,225
為什麼我的心情沒有好起來？
Why don't I feel better?

1383
02:00:48,403 --> 02:00:50,701
女孩們穿著白裙
Girls in white dresses

1384
02:00:50,973 --> 02:00:54,067
佩著藍緞帶
With blue satin sashes

1385
02:00:54,343 --> 02:00:59,975
雪花落在我的鼻子和睫毛上
Snowflakes that stay On my nose and eyelashes

1386
02:01:00,349 --> 02:01:03,512
-銀白色的冬天… -?莉亞小姐回來了
- Silver white winters... - Fraulein Maria's back!

1387
02:01:03,719 --> 02:01:05,016
溶化成春天
...that melt into springs

1388
02:01:05,420 --> 02:01:08,685
這些都是我喜愛的事物
These are a few of my favorite things

1389
02:01:08,924 --> 02:01:12,018
當狗咬時，當蜂蟄時
When the dog bites When the bee stings

1390
02:01:12,227 --> 02:01:14,354
當我感覺傷心時
When I'm feeling sad

1391
02:01:14,863 --> 02:01:17,832
只要想起我最喜愛的事物
I simply remember my favorite things

1392
02:01:18,100 --> 02:01:20,364
我的心情就不會…
And then I don't feel

1393
02:01:20,569 --> 02:01:27,338
如此糟了
So bad

1394
02:01:27,576 --> 02:01:30,602
-孩子們，看到你們真高興 -我們很想念你
- Children, I'm so glad to see you. - We missed you.

1395
02:01:30,846 --> 02:01:31,835
我想念你們
I missed you.

1396
02:01:32,114 --> 02:01:34,241
-寇特，你好嗎？ -很餓
- Kurt, how are you? - Hungry.

1397
02:01:35,784 --> 02:01:38,412
-葛特兒，你的手指怎麼了？ -被割傷了
- What happened to your finger? - It got caught.

1398
02:01:38,687 --> 02:01:40,848
-被什麼割的？ -費端克的牙齒
- Caught in what? - Friedrich's teeth.

1399
02:01:42,090 --> 02:01:44,251
-莉莎，你好嗎？ -還好啦
- Liesl, you all right? - Just fair.

1400
02:01:44,459 --> 02:01:47,451
-最近有沒有電報來？ -什麼都沒有
- Any telegrams been delivered lately? - None at all.

1401
02:01:47,696 --> 02:01:51,132
但是我在學習接受現實 我在期待學校開學的日子
But I'm learning to accept it. I'll be glad when school begins.

1402
02:01:51,433 --> 02:01:56,132
莉莎，你不能用學校作為逃避 問題的地方，你必須面對問題
Liesl, you can't use school to escape your problems. You have to face them.

1403
02:01:56,371 --> 02:01:57,804
我要告訴你們很多事
I have so much to tell you.

1404
02:01:58,073 --> 02:02:00,064
我們也有許多事要告訴你
We have things to tell you too.

1405
02:02:00,409 --> 02:02:04,106
最重要的是，爸爸要結婚了
The most important thing is that Father is going to be married.

1406
02:02:04,313 --> 02:02:05,371
結婚？
Married?

1407
02:02:05,714 --> 02:02:07,739
是的，是和男爵夫人
Yes, to Baroness Schraeder.

1408
02:02:15,657 --> 02:02:17,215
哦，我知道了
Oh, I see.

1409
02:02:19,061 --> 02:02:22,428
爸爸，看！ ?莉亞回來了！
Father, look! Fraulein Maria's back!

1410
02:02:22,664 --> 02:02:24,723
?莉亞從修道院回來了
Fraulein Maria's back from the abbey.

1411
02:02:26,935 --> 02:02:27,993
艦長你好
Good evening, captain.

1412
02:02:29,471 --> 02:02:30,768
你好
Good evening.

1413
02:02:33,308 --> 02:02:35,139
大家都進去吃晚餐
Everyone inside for dinner.

1414
02:02:35,444 --> 02:02:37,002
晚飯，太好了！
Dinner!

1415
02:02:46,355 --> 02:02:51,088
你不辭而別 甚至沒向小孩們道別
You left without saying goodbye. Even to the children.

1416
02:02:52,094 --> 02:02:53,618
是我的錯，請原諒我
It was wrong of me. Forgive me.

1417
02:02:55,664 --> 02:02:56,824
為什麼要如此？
Why did you?

1418
02:02:57,032 --> 02:02:59,865
請不要問我 反正原因已經不存在了
Please don't ask me. The reason no longer exists.

1419
02:03:01,036 --> 02:03:04,130
?莉亞小姐，你回來了
Fraulein Maria, you've returned.

1420
02:03:05,374 --> 02:03:07,171
蓋爾，這不是很好嗎？
Isn't it wonderful, Georg?

1421
02:03:10,479 --> 02:03:12,709
男爵夫人，我祝福你幸福快樂
I wish you every happiness, baroness.

1422
02:03:12,948 --> 02:03:15,644
你也是，艦長 孩子們告訴我你們要結婚了
You too, captain. The children say you're to marry.

1423
02:03:15,884 --> 02:03:17,010
謝謝你，親愛的
Thank you, my dear.

1424
02:03:19,554 --> 02:03:23,115
你會留下嗎？
You are back to stay?

1425
02:03:25,193 --> 02:03:28,526
只待到下一位老師來為止
Only until arrangements can be made for another governess.

1426
02:04:24,219 --> 02:04:25,846
原來你在這裡
There you are.

1427
02:04:40,235 --> 02:04:42,703
我真的要跟你的廚師談談
I must speak to cook about the schnitzel.

1428
02:04:42,971 --> 02:04:46,270
食物太好吃會影響我的身材
It is entirely too delicious for my figure.

1429
02:04:46,708 --> 02:04:49,643
也讓你在餐桌上 沒說很多話
And it makes you much too quiet at the dinner table.

1430
02:04:49,911 --> 02:04:51,902
是不是酒的關係？
Or was it the wine?

1431
02:04:52,147 --> 02:04:53,978
一定是
Undoubtedly the wine.

1432
02:04:56,551 --> 02:04:58,815
你不知道為了要送你
You have no idea the trouble I'm having...

1433
02:04:59,087 --> 02:05:01,817
一件結婚禮物 我費盡了多少心思
...trying to decide on a wedding present for you.

1434
02:05:02,124 --> 02:05:04,285
我明白，你有我已經足夠
Oh, I know. I'm enough.

1435
02:05:04,559 --> 02:05:08,154
但是我一定要送你點小玩意
But I do want you to have some little trifle for the occasion.

1436
02:05:08,397 --> 02:05:10,729
我首先想到的是鋼筆
At first I thought of a fountain pen...

1437
02:05:10,966 --> 02:05:13,230
但是你已有一支
...but you've already got one.

1438
02:05:13,502 --> 02:05:16,437
然後我想送你 一幢法國南部的別墅
Then I thought perhaps a villa in the south of France...

1439
02:05:16,671 --> 02:05:19,333
但是它很難包裝起來
...but they are so difficult to gift-wrap.

1440
02:05:19,608 --> 02:05:22,008
你覺得遊艇好嗎？
Oh, Georg, how do you feel about yachts?

1441
02:05:22,310 --> 02:05:24,574
可以暢遊地中海的那種
A long, sleek one for the Mediterranean...

1442
02:05:24,813 --> 02:05:27,577
或是放在浴缸中的那種
...or a tiny one for your bathtub, huh?

1443
02:05:29,751 --> 02:05:31,776
-艾莎 -我們要去哪渡蜜月？
- Elsa. - Where to go on our honeymoon?

1444
02:05:32,020 --> 02:05:33,612
這可真是個難題了
Now, that's a real problem.

1445
02:05:33,822 --> 02:05:37,189
我想環遊世界會很棒
A trip around the world would be lovely. And then I said:

1446
02:05:37,492 --> 02:05:40,325
但一定會有更好的地方可以去
"Oh, Elsa, there must be someplace better to go."

1447
02:05:40,595 --> 02:05:43,029
-但別擔心… -艾莎
- But don't worry, darling, I'Il... - Elsa.

1448
02:05:43,698 --> 02:05:44,960
是的
Yes, Georg.

1449
02:05:45,967 --> 02:05:47,298
這是沒有用的
It's no use...

1450
02:05:48,503 --> 02:05:49,868
你和我的關係
...you and I.

1451
02:05:51,440 --> 02:05:54,671
我一直都沒有坦誠面對
I'm being dishonest to both of us...

1452
02:05:56,011 --> 02:05:57,672
你和我的關係
...and utterly unfair to you.

1453
02:06:02,951 --> 02:06:05,681
-當兩個人談論到婚嫁時 -不要
- When two people talk of marriage... - No, don't.

1454
02:06:06,555 --> 02:06:08,648
不要再說了，拜託你
Don't say another word, please.

1455
02:06:11,960 --> 02:06:16,988
我也在想其他的事
You see, there are other things I've been thinking of.

1456
02:06:17,899 --> 02:06:22,632
雖然我喜歡你 但是我真的不認為你適合我
Fond as I am of you, I really don't think you're the right man for me.

1457
02:06:25,173 --> 02:06:27,664
你太獨立了
You're much too independent.

1458
02:06:27,976 --> 02:06:32,675
而我要一個非常需要我的人
And I need someone who needs me desperately...

1459
02:06:32,981 --> 02:06:35,973
或最起碼是非常需要我的錢
...or at least needs my money desperately.

1460
02:06:38,153 --> 02:06:43,056
我們在一起的每一分鐘 我都很快樂，為此我謝謝你
I've enjoyed every moment we've had together and I do thank you for that.

1461
02:06:45,827 --> 02:06:47,727
失陪一下
Now, if you'll forgive me...

1462
02:06:47,929 --> 02:06:49,988
我現在要進去 收拾我的行李
...I'll go inside, pack my little bags...

1463
02:06:50,232 --> 02:06:52,723
回到我原屬的地方，維也納
...and return to Vienna where I belong.

1464
02:06:58,106 --> 02:06:59,937
那邊有個人
And somewhere out there...

1465
02:07:00,242 --> 02:07:04,611
是位年輕小姐，我想
...is a young lady who, I think...

1466
02:07:04,880 --> 02:07:06,108
她做不成修女了
...will never be a nun.

1467
02:07:18,260 --> 02:07:20,592
親愛的，再見了
Auf Wiedersehen, darling.

1468
02:07:46,321 --> 02:07:47,481
哈囉
Hello.

1469
02:07:53,295 --> 02:07:56,890
我想我可能會在這裡找到你
I thought I just might find you here.

1470
02:08:01,069 --> 02:08:03,333
你有什麼事找我嗎？
Was there something you wanted?

1471
02:08:03,772 --> 02:08:06,900
沒有，沒有，請坐下
No, no, no. Sit down, please.

1472
02:08:07,842 --> 02:08:09,173
請坐
Please.

1473
02:08:14,316 --> 02:08:15,647
我可以坐嗎？
May I?

1474
02:08:28,029 --> 02:08:32,762
我在想… 在思索兩件事情
You know, I was thinking and I was wondering two things:

1475
02:08:33,935 --> 02:08:38,167
為什麼你逃回修道院？
Why did you run away to the abbey?

1476
02:08:39,007 --> 02:08:43,671
還有，是什麼事又讓你回來？
And what was it that made you come back?

1477
02:08:45,347 --> 02:08:49,807
這個，我有責任要完成
Well, I had an obligation to fulfill...

1478
02:08:50,018 --> 02:08:52,145
我回來履行的
...and I came back to fulfill it.

1479
02:08:52,787 --> 02:08:54,220
只是這樣嗎？
Is that all?

1480
02:08:55,557 --> 02:08:57,718
還有，我想念孩子們
And I missed the children.

1481
02:08:58,059 --> 02:08:59,219
是的
Yes.

1482
02:09:00,495 --> 02:09:03,396
-只有小孩們？ -不…是的
- Only the children? - No. Yes.

1483
02:09:03,632 --> 02:09:07,466
-我可以想念他們，對嗎？ -對…當然可以了
- Isn't it right that I missed them? - Oh, yes. Yes, of course.

1484
02:09:07,669 --> 02:09:10,297
我只是想你或許會…
I was only hoping that perhaps you...

1485
02:09:11,406 --> 02:09:13,169
或許你會…
Perhaps you might...

1486
02:09:14,909 --> 02:09:16,137
怎樣？
Yes?

1487
02:09:17,912 --> 02:09:23,214
這個… 當你離開後一切都變了
Well, nothing was the same when you were away...

1488
02:09:23,985 --> 02:09:27,216
如果你又再離去 我們又會再度失落
...and it'll be all wrong again after you leave...

1489
02:09:27,422 --> 02:09:32,086
我只是想 也許你可以改變心意留下來
...and I just thought perhaps you might change your mind.

1490
02:09:36,164 --> 02:09:40,396
我想男爵夫人一定會把 一切的事情都安排得很好
Well, I'm sure the baroness will be able to make things fine for you.

1491
02:09:40,669 --> 02:09:42,000
?莉亞
Maria...

1492
02:09:44,105 --> 02:09:47,597
-再也沒有什麼男爵夫人了 -沒有了嗎？
- There isn't going to be any baroness. - There isn't?

1493
02:09:50,011 --> 02:09:51,376
沒有
No.

1494
02:09:51,680 --> 02:09:53,443
我不明白
I don't understand.

1495
02:09:55,850 --> 02:09:59,946
我們已經解除婚約了
Well, we've called off our engagement, you see, and...

1496
02:10:00,221 --> 02:10:03,679
-我很難過 -對，真的嗎？
- Oh, I'm sorry. - Yes. You are?

1497
02:10:04,859 --> 02:10:06,952
-真的？ -是的
- You did? - Yes.

1498
02:10:08,096 --> 02:10:12,624
你不能和一個人結婚…
Well, you can't marry someone when you're...

1499
02:10:15,203 --> 02:10:17,262
卻又愛著另一個人
...in love with someone else...

1500
02:10:20,642 --> 02:10:22,075
你可以嗎？
...can you?

1501
02:10:56,945 --> 02:10:59,243
院長常說
The Reverend Mother always says:

1502
02:10:59,481 --> 02:11:02,917
“當主關上門時 他會在某處打開窗子的”
"When the Lord closes a door, somewhere He opens a window."

1503
02:11:11,006 --> 02:11:14,032
院長還說了什麼？
What else does the Reverend Mother say?

1504
02:11:14,976 --> 02:11:17,376
你需要尋求你自己的生命
That you have to look for your life.

1505
02:11:19,047 --> 02:11:21,607
這是不是你回來的原因？
Is that why you came back?

1506
02:11:25,654 --> 02:11:27,121
你找到了嗎？
And have you found it...

1507
02:11:28,123 --> 02:11:29,283
?莉亞
...Maria?

1508
02:11:31,059 --> 02:11:33,050
我想我找到了
I think I have.

1509
02:11:35,797 --> 02:11:37,196
我知道我已找到了
I know I have.

1510
02:11:39,701 --> 02:11:41,362
我愛你
I love you.

1511
02:11:45,340 --> 02:11:47,205
這種事情會發生在我身上嗎？
Oh, can this be happening to me?

1512
02:11:50,579 --> 02:11:55,983
或許我的童年是不愉快的
Perhaps I had a wicked childhood

1513
02:11:57,486 --> 02:12:02,719
或許我的青春期是悲慘的
Perhaps I had a miserable youth

1514
02:12:04,593 --> 02:12:10,532
但在我又不愉快 又可悲的過去
But somewhere In my wicked, miserable past

1515
02:12:11,032 --> 02:12:16,834
卻總有一刻是真實的
There must have been a moment of truth

1516
02:12:17,772 --> 02:12:24,541
你就站在這裡 愛著我
For here you are Standing there loving me

1517
02:12:25,280 --> 02:12:31,276
不管應該與否
Whether or not you should

1518
02:12:31,920 --> 02:12:38,723
因此在我的童年或少年時
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1519
02:12:39,594 --> 02:12:47,228
一定是做過了什麼好事
I must have done something good

1520
02:12:48,470 --> 02:12:51,439
萬事皆有因
Nothing comes from nothing

1521
02:12:52,574 --> 02:12:56,442
不會無中生有
Nothing ever could

1522
02:12:57,279 --> 02:13:06,153
因此在我的童年或少年時
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1523
02:13:07,722 --> 02:13:17,222
一定是做過了什麼好事
I must have done something good

1524
02:13:18,099 --> 02:13:22,934
你知道我是何時開始 愛上你的？
Do you know when I first started loving you?

1525
02:13:23,338 --> 02:13:27,240
那天晚餐 你坐在那可笑的松果上
That night at dinner, when you sat on that ridiculous pine cone.

1526
02:13:27,475 --> 02:13:28,772
什麼？
What?

1527
02:13:30,111 --> 02:13:33,569
當你吹著那個傻哨子時 我就愛上你了
I knew the first time you blew that silly whistle.

1528
02:13:34,482 --> 02:13:36,473
哦，我的愛
Oh, my love.

1529
02:13:40,255 --> 02:13:48,162
你就站在這裡 愛著我
For here you are Standing there loving me

1530
02:13:50,131 --> 02:13:55,967
不管應該與否
Whether or not you should

1531
02:13:57,339 --> 02:14:04,370
因此在我的童年或少年時
So somewhere in my youth or childhood

1532
02:14:05,180 --> 02:14:12,882
一定是做過了什麼好事
I must have done something good

1533
02:14:14,055 --> 02:14:17,547
萬事皆有因
Nothing comes from nothing

1534
02:14:18,293 --> 02:14:21,319
不會無中生有
Nothing ever could

1535
02:14:21,563 --> 02:14:27,365
因此在我的童年…
So somewhere in my youth...

1536
02:14:27,636 --> 02:14:29,866
或少年時
...or childhood

1537
02:14:32,974 --> 02:14:39,504
一定是做過了
I must have done something

1538
02:14:41,549 --> 02:14:54,189
什麼好事
Something good

1539
02:15:00,902 --> 02:15:02,426
?莉亞
Maria.

1540
02:15:04,272 --> 02:15:08,868
我要徵求誰的同意才能娶你？
Is there anyone I should go to, to ask permission to marry you?

1541
02:15:12,781 --> 02:15:15,341
-為什麼我們不問… -孩子們？
- Why don't we ask... - The children?

1542
02:17:03,858 --> 02:17:07,885
你要如何處理 像?莉亞這樣的問題人物？
How do you solve a problem like Maria?

1543
02:17:08,696 --> 02:17:12,393
你要如何摘下浮雲 然後釘牢？
How do you catch a cloud And pin it down?

1544
02:17:13,368 --> 02:17:17,532
你要如何用言語形容她？
How do you find a word That means Maria?

1545
02:17:17,972 --> 02:17:18,961
搗蛋鬼
A flibbertigibbet

1546
02:17:19,207 --> 02:17:22,472
鬼靈精 小丑
A will-o'-the-wisp A clown

1547
02:17:22,677 --> 02:17:27,239
許多事你們想告訴她
Many a thing you know You'd like to tell her

1548
02:17:27,682 --> 02:17:31,709
許多事她該明瞭
Many a thing she ought to understand

1549
02:17:32,420 --> 02:17:36,720
但如何使她停下聽你說完？
But how do you make her stay And listen to all you say?

1550
02:17:37,091 --> 02:17:41,027
如何使海浪停留在沙灘上？
How do you keep a wave upon the sand?

1551
02:17:41,362 --> 02:17:46,356
你要如何處理 像?莉亞這樣的問題人物？
Oh, how do you solve A problem like Maria?

1552
02:17:46,734 --> 02:17:53,367
如何使月光在掌中停留？
How do you hold a moonbeam In your hand?

1553
02:19:59,467 --> 02:20:01,025
你好
Herr Detweiler!

1554
02:20:03,638 --> 02:20:06,300
-希特勒萬歲 -午安，吉勒先生
- Heil Hitler. - Oh, good afternoon, Herr Zeller.

1555
02:20:06,541 --> 02:20:09,840
或許你還不知道 我現在是這裡的監督
Perhaps you've not heard. I am now the Gauleiter.

1556
02:20:10,144 --> 02:20:11,668
希特勒萬歲
Heil Hitler.

1557
02:20:12,580 --> 02:20:13,740
希特勒萬歲
Heil Hitler.

1558
02:20:14,048 --> 02:20:16,312
我剛從范崔普家來
I've come from Captain von Trapp's house.

1559
02:20:16,751 --> 02:20:20,346
合併後只有他家不掛…
The only one in the area not flying the Third Reich flag...

1560
02:20:20,588 --> 02:20:21,850
德國旗
...since the Anschluss.

1561
02:20:22,056 --> 02:20:24,217
-但是我們必須解決那問題 -我不…
- But we have dealt with that. - I don't...

1562
02:20:24,492 --> 02:20:27,427
管家告訴我會在這找到你
The housekeeper told me that I would find you here.

1563
02:20:27,695 --> 02:20:29,390
這是那個女人 給我的唯一情報
The only thing she'd tell me.

1564
02:20:29,897 --> 02:20:32,422
你在找什麼情報？
What kind of information are you looking for?

1565
02:20:32,700 --> 02:20:34,565
艦長何時會回來？
When will the captain return?

1566
02:20:35,103 --> 02:20:39,039
他去渡蜜月了 他沒和我們聯絡
Well, he's on his honeymoon trip. He's not been in touch with us.

1567
02:20:39,273 --> 02:20:44,108
你要我相信艦長一個多月 沒和他的孩子們聯絡？
Am I to believe he hasn't communicated with his children in over a month?

1568
02:20:44,379 --> 02:20:46,279
監督，你認識多少人…
How many men do you know...

1569
02:20:46,547 --> 02:20:49,846
會在渡蜜月時和孩子聯絡？
...who communicate with their children while honeymooning?

1570
02:20:50,752 --> 02:20:54,449
當他回來時 我們希望他接受新政府的職位
Upon his return, he'll fill his proper position in the new order.

1571
02:20:54,756 --> 02:20:57,122
當然了，多謝你…
Naturally. And may I congratulate you...

1572
02:20:57,358 --> 02:21:02,022
和你的人們允許今晚可以 如期舉行音樂節
...and your people in allowing the festival to go on tonight as planned.

1573
02:21:02,563 --> 02:21:06,021
為何我們會不允許？ 奧地利什麼都沒改變
Why should it not go on? Nothing in Austria has changed.

1574
02:21:06,267 --> 02:21:09,668
唱歌和音樂可宣告世界
Singing and music will show this to the world.

1575
02:21:09,871 --> 02:21:11,566
奧地利依然如昔
Austria is the same.

1576
02:21:12,440 --> 02:21:13,805
希特勒萬歲
Heil Hitler.

1577
02:21:15,977 --> 02:21:17,569
希特勒萬歲
Heil Hitler.

1578
02:21:19,247 --> 02:21:20,475
走吧，我們回家去
Come, let's go home.

1579
02:21:20,715 --> 02:21:24,207
-為何他這麼凶？ -這些日子大家都很凶
- Why was he so cross? - Everybody's cross these days.

1580
02:21:24,419 --> 02:21:27,786
也許是旗上的黑蜘蛛 使人們緊張起來
Maybe the flag with the black spider makes people nervous.

1581
02:21:27,989 --> 02:21:30,924
-爸爸是不是有麻煩了？ -他是有選擇的
- Will Father be in trouble? - He doesn't have to be.

1582
02:21:31,159 --> 02:21:33,889
這些日子以來最重要的 是和大家和睦相處
The thing to do is to get along with everybody.

1583
02:21:34,128 --> 02:21:36,323
我要你們記住 尤其在今晚的演唱會上
Remember that tonight at the concert.

1584
02:21:36,564 --> 02:21:39,465
今晚我們真的要 在一大堆人面前唱歌？
Are we really going to sing before a lot of people?

1585
02:21:39,667 --> 02:21:41,760
看，范崔普家庭音樂團 名字是…
Look. The von Trapp Family Singers:

1586
02:21:41,969 --> 02:21:46,565
莉莎，費瑞克，露易莎，碧姬塔 寇特，?塔，葛特兒
Liesl, Friedrich, Louisa, Brigitta, Kurt, Marta and Gretl.

1587
02:21:46,774 --> 02:21:51,143
-為什麼我總是排在最後？ -因為你是最重要的
- Why am I always last? - Because you are the most important.

1588
02:21:51,846 --> 02:21:53,473
我們走吧
There we go.

1589
02:21:59,353 --> 02:22:02,811
你確定爸爸 會准許我們公開演唱？
Are you sure Father will approve of our singing in public?

1590
02:22:03,024 --> 02:22:05,322
他會很高興並引以為傲的
He'll be pleased and proud.

1591
02:22:05,793 --> 02:22:08,261
-莉莎，你覺得如此嗎？ -你們不信任我嗎？
- Liesl, do you think so? - Don't you trust me?

1592
02:22:08,463 --> 02:22:09,487
不信任
No.

1593
02:22:09,697 --> 02:22:11,790
你是個很聰明的女孩
You're a very intelligent girl.

1594
02:22:12,333 --> 02:22:14,494
莉莎…
Liesl. Liesl!

1595
02:22:15,436 --> 02:22:16,630
勞夫
Rolfe!

1596
02:22:17,638 --> 02:22:19,663
很高興見到你，已經…
I'm so glad to see you. It's been su...

1597
02:22:19,874 --> 02:22:20,966
午安
Good afternoon.

1598
02:22:21,375 --> 02:22:24,310
請你把這電報交給你父親
Give this to your father as soon as he's home.

1599
02:22:24,979 --> 02:22:26,844
-他正在渡蜜月呢 -我知道
- He's on his honeymoon. - I know.

1600
02:22:27,048 --> 02:22:30,381
-你知道？ -幹我們這行的事事都要知道
- You do? - We make it our business to know all.

1601
02:22:31,119 --> 02:22:33,679
-誰是“我們”？ -你要肯定他會收到
- Who's "we"? - See that he gets it.

1602
02:22:33,888 --> 02:22:36,220
-這是什麼？ -是從柏林來的電報
- What is it? - It's a telegram from Berlin.

1603
02:22:37,058 --> 02:22:39,549
你不要親自來交給他嗎？
Don't you want to deliver it yourself?

1604
02:22:40,027 --> 02:22:42,655
我有更重要的事
I'm occupied with more important matters.

1605
02:22:42,864 --> 02:22:45,355
你父親也最好能知輕重
And your father had better be too.

1606
02:22:45,633 --> 02:22:47,123
但是，勞夫！
But, Rolfe!

1607
02:23:10,224 --> 02:23:11,885
爸爸…
Father!

1608
02:23:12,160 --> 02:23:14,822
-我們沒料到你這麼快回來 -哈囉…
- We didn't expect you so soon. - Hello, hello!

1609
02:23:15,062 --> 02:23:17,860
我們以為你下星期回來！
We didn't expect you home until next week!

1610
02:23:18,065 --> 02:23:23,503
-有在巴黎給我們買手信嗎？ -你好嗎？
- Did you bring souvenirs from Paris? - Hello! How are you?

1611
02:23:24,605 --> 02:23:25,902
你們為什麼沒有打給我們？
Why didn't you call us?

1612
02:23:26,107 --> 02:23:28,041
我們試過了，但是不通
We couldn't get through.

1613
02:23:28,342 --> 02:23:30,276
這個我也沒奈何
I had nothing to do with that.

1614
02:23:30,545 --> 02:23:32,570
我們儘快趕回來了
We came back as fast as we could.

1615
02:23:32,880 --> 02:23:35,041
我們很想念你們
Well, well, well! We missed you!

1616
02:23:35,283 --> 02:23:37,717
-我們很想你們 -我們很想親你們
- We missed you! - We missed kissing you.

1617
02:23:37,919 --> 02:23:40,752
我想念你們早上的噪音
We missed all the noise in the morning.

1618
02:23:41,022 --> 02:23:45,220
-最想念的是你們的歌聲 -你們回來得正巧
- Mostly, we missed hearing you sing. - Oh, you came back just in time.

1619
02:23:45,426 --> 02:23:47,189
看這個，瑪莉亞小姐…
Look, Fraulein Maria...

1620
02:23:47,395 --> 02:23:49,022
我是說媽媽
I mean Mother.

1621
02:23:49,430 --> 02:23:51,921
我們今晚會在音樂節唱歌
We're going to sing in the festival tonight.

1622
02:23:52,133 --> 02:23:54,260
我們過得很快樂
We've been having a lovely time!

1623
02:23:54,535 --> 02:23:56,594
我們練習了一天
We've been rehearsing all...

1624
02:23:58,105 --> 02:24:00,437
驚喜！驚喜！
Surprise! Surprise!

1625
02:24:01,108 --> 02:24:03,599
裡面有令你們驚喜的東西
Surprises for you on the terrace.

1626
02:24:06,647 --> 02:24:08,046
我們到裡面去談這個
We'll talk about this.

1627
02:24:08,249 --> 02:24:12,549
我本想要告訴你，但是你不在 我只有在最後一刻自作主張了
I would've told you but you were away. I had to make a last-minute decision.

1628
02:24:12,820 --> 02:24:15,311
我還算好運氣 總算趕得及報名
I was fortunate to enter them at all.

1629
02:24:15,556 --> 02:24:20,289
他們必會成為話題的 試想一個家庭中的七個小孩
They'll be the talk of the festival. Imagine, seven children in one family!

1630
02:24:20,494 --> 02:24:22,121
麥斯
Max!

1631
02:24:22,730 --> 02:24:25,563
我記得我以前 向你解釋得很清楚…
Somehow I recall having made it quite clear to you...

1632
02:24:25,833 --> 02:24:28,495
我對於我家的小孩 在外面演唱的事的感覺
...how I feel about my family singing in public!

1633
02:24:28,769 --> 02:24:30,464
但是委員會聽過他們唱 非常的感動
The committee was enchanted.

1634
02:24:30,671 --> 02:24:33,834
-他們說了什麼？ -沒聽過這麼熱情的聲音
- What did they say? - I have never heard such enthusiasm.

1635
02:24:34,108 --> 02:24:38,408
-就一次好不好？ -絕對不可能
- Don't you think just this once...? - Absolutely out of the question.

1636
02:24:38,646 --> 02:24:42,776
-這是為了奧地利 -為了奧地利？
- Georg, this is for Austria. - For Austria?

1637
02:24:43,150 --> 02:24:46,415
-已經沒有奧地利了！ -但是德奧合併得很和平
- There is no Austria! - But the Anschluss was peaceful.

1638
02:24:46,654 --> 02:24:50,112
-我們應感到欣慰 -欣慰？
- Let's at least be grateful for that. - Grateful?

1639
02:24:51,993 --> 02:24:53,654
你知道嗎？麥斯
You know, Max...

1640
02:24:54,528 --> 02:24:57,793
有時候我無法相信 自己認識你
...sometimes I don't believe I know you.

1641
02:25:00,468 --> 02:25:01,833
爸爸，我忘了
Father, I forgot.

1642
02:25:02,670 --> 02:25:04,262
這是給你的
This is for you.

1643
02:25:14,048 --> 02:25:18,041
?莉亞，至少他必須假裝 和這些人合作
Maria, he has got to at least pretend to work with these people.

1644
02:25:18,319 --> 02:25:19,843
你必須說服他
You must convince him.

1645
02:25:20,054 --> 02:25:22,818
我不能要求他聽我的話
Max, I can't ask him to be less than he is.

1646
02:25:23,057 --> 02:25:26,356
那麼我和他談 如果孩子們不參加音樂節
Then I'll talk to him. If the children don't sing, well...

1647
02:25:26,627 --> 02:25:28,857
是一樣對奧地利有損的事
...it will be a reflection on Austria.

1648
02:25:29,664 --> 02:25:33,031
對我也沒有好處
Oh, I know. It wouldn't do me any good either.

1649
02:25:38,205 --> 02:25:40,867
媽，可以這樣叫你真好
Mother? That sounds so nice.

1650
02:25:41,142 --> 02:25:43,872
-我喜歡叫你媽 -我喜歡聽你叫
- I like calling you "Mother." - I like hearing it.

1651
02:25:44,078 --> 02:25:47,809
你很愛爸爸，我看得出來
You love Father very much. I can tell you do.

1652
02:25:48,015 --> 02:25:48,811
非常愛他
Very much.

1653
02:25:49,083 --> 02:25:52,382
媽，當你認為你愛某個人時 你要怎麼辦？
Mother, what do you do when you think you love someone?

1654
02:25:53,087 --> 02:25:58,389
我是說當你不再愛他 或他不再愛你時
I mean, when you stop loving someone or he stops loving you?

1655
02:26:00,995 --> 02:26:03,054
你會哭一場
Well, you cry a little.

1656
02:26:03,497 --> 02:26:05,590
等待太陽出來
Then you wait for the sun to come out.

1657
02:26:05,900 --> 02:26:07,231
快樂的日子終會再來
It always does.

1658
02:26:07,501 --> 02:26:11,062
有許多事情我認為我應該知道 但我卻不知道
There are so many things I think I should know but I don't.

1659
02:26:11,272 --> 02:26:13,240
-真的不知道 -怎麼說？
- I really don't. - How can you?

1660
02:26:13,507 --> 02:26:15,702
有時我覺得世界就快完了
Sometimes I feel the world is ending.

1661
02:26:15,943 --> 02:26:19,174
-然後你覺得這才剛開始？ -是的
- Then you feel it's just beginning? - Yes!

1662
02:26:19,380 --> 02:26:23,612
我以前也這麼覺得 對你，一切會很好的
It was that way with me. And for you it will be just as wonderful.

1663
02:26:24,285 --> 02:26:26,185
你真的認為如此？
Do you really think so?

1664
02:26:27,088 --> 02:26:31,024
你16歲，快17歲了
When you're 16 going on 17

1665
02:26:31,292 --> 02:26:34,887
人生才要開始
Waiting for life to start

1666
02:26:35,563 --> 02:26:39,397
一個讓你留下好印象的人
Somebody kind Who touches your mind

1667
02:26:39,633 --> 02:26:43,933
會突然觸動你的心靈
Will suddenly touch your heart

1668
02:26:44,372 --> 02:26:46,067
當這事…
When that happens

1669
02:26:46,540 --> 02:26:48,474
發生之後
After it happens

1670
02:26:48,709 --> 02:26:52,577
一切都改變了
Nothing is quite the same

1671
02:26:52,813 --> 02:26:54,371
我知道…
Somehow I know

1672
02:26:54,648 --> 02:26:56,775
我會立刻走過去
I'll jump up and go

1673
02:26:56,984 --> 02:27:01,284
若他呼喚我的名字
If ever he calls my name

1674
02:27:01,555 --> 02:27:05,457
你舊日對生命的看法會變改
Gone are your old ideas of life

1675
02:27:05,726 --> 02:27:09,924
那些舊念頭都變得黯淡
The old ideas grow dim

1676
02:27:10,164 --> 02:27:14,567
你會發現你已為人妻
Lo and behold You're someone's wife

1677
02:27:15,503 --> 02:27:21,499
你完全屬於他
And you belong to him

1678
02:27:21,809 --> 02:27:26,109
你會以為這種歷險
You may think this kind of adventure

1679
02:27:26,313 --> 02:27:30,181
永不會發生在自己身上
Never may come to you

1680
02:27:31,285 --> 02:27:36,655
親愛的已16歲，快17歲了
Darling, 16 going on 17

1681
02:27:37,491 --> 02:27:41,621
耐心等一年…
Wait a year...

1682
02:27:42,430 --> 02:27:47,663
-我會等一年 -或兩年吧
- I'll wait a year ...or two

1683
02:27:48,102 --> 02:27:55,440
只要等一年…
Just wait a year...

1684
02:27:56,310 --> 02:28:04,945
或兩年
...or two

1685
02:28:07,354 --> 02:28:08,946
莉莎
Liesl.

1686
02:28:25,406 --> 02:28:26,737
什麼事情？
What is it?

1687
02:28:27,675 --> 02:28:29,040
是柏林
Berlin.

1688
02:28:29,510 --> 02:28:31,375
他們給我委派了一項任命
They've offered me a commission.

1689
02:28:31,645 --> 02:28:34,170
並要求我馬上接受
I've been requested to accept immediately...

1690
02:28:34,415 --> 02:28:38,408
明天到北萊梅港海軍基地報到
...and report to their naval base at Bremerhaven tomorrow.

1691
02:28:39,019 --> 02:28:43,012
我就知道這種事會發生 沒料到這麼快
I knew this would happen. I didn't think it would be so soon.

1692
02:28:43,257 --> 02:28:46,749
拒絕的話，全家會遭到懲罰
To refuse them would be fatal for all of us.

1693
02:28:47,995 --> 02:28:51,761
加入的話後果更難想像
And joining them would be unthinkable.

1694
02:28:57,938 --> 02:28:59,701
叫小孩們都過來
Get the children all together.

1695
02:29:00,040 --> 02:29:03,237
別說讓他們擔心的話 只要讓他們準備好
Don't say anything to worry them. Just get them ready.

1696
02:29:04,211 --> 02:29:06,577
我們必須離開奧地利
We've got to get out of Austria...

1697
02:29:08,249 --> 02:29:09,910
還有這所房子
...and this house...

1698
02:29:12,253 --> 02:29:13,686
就在今晚
...tonight.

1699
02:29:57,598 --> 02:29:59,998
今晚你們不唱了
This strains my back and breaks my heart...

1700
02:30:00,267 --> 02:30:03,100
真是讓我傷心難過
...when I think of the children missing the festival.

1701
02:30:03,404 --> 02:30:06,066
你宣佈的時候 我們就越過邊界了
By your announcement we'll be over the border.

1702
02:30:06,307 --> 02:30:08,741
我希望你會感激我所做的犧牲
Do you appreciate the sacrifice I'm making?

1703
02:30:08,943 --> 02:30:10,240
你沒有選擇
You have no choice.

1704
02:30:10,477 --> 02:30:13,310
我知道，這就是我會這樣做的原因
I know. That's why I'm making it.

1705
02:30:14,014 --> 02:30:16,141
爸爸為何不發動引擎？
Why doesn't Father turn the motor on?

1706
02:30:16,350 --> 02:30:19,786
因為他不要任何人聽到
Because he doesn't want anyone to hear us.

1707
02:30:23,424 --> 02:30:25,858
管家們會說什麼？
What will Frau Schmidt and Franz say?

1708
02:30:26,126 --> 02:30:29,653
他們可以老實回答 他們什麼都不知道
They'll be able to answer honestly they didn't know anything.

1709
02:30:29,863 --> 02:30:34,095
-我們會再回來嗎？ -莉莎，我希望會有這一天
- Will we be coming back here? - Someday, Liesl. I do hope someday.

1710
02:30:34,335 --> 02:30:39,272
爸爸和麥伯伯 要一直推車到瑞士嗎？
Are Father and Uncle Max going to push the car all the way to Switzerland?

1711
02:31:06,066 --> 02:31:08,466
艦長，你的車是不是有毛病？
Something wrong with your car, captain?

1712
02:31:08,802 --> 02:31:11,066
是的，車子無法啟動
Yes, we couldn't get it started.

1713
02:31:14,842 --> 02:31:16,070
卡爾
Karl.

1714
02:31:18,045 --> 02:31:21,537
替艦長把車修好 好讓其啟動
Fix Captain von Trapp's car so that it will start.

1715
02:31:44,738 --> 02:31:46,535
做得好
Excellent, Karl.

1716
02:31:49,910 --> 02:31:53,073
我沒問你和你的家人要到哪
I've not asked you where you and your family are going.

1717
02:31:53,580 --> 02:31:55,707
你也沒問我為何在此
Nor have you asked me why I'm here.

1718
02:31:55,916 --> 02:31:59,682
我想我們兩個都沒什麼好奇心
Apparently we both suffer from a deplorable lack of curiosity.

1719
02:32:00,554 --> 02:32:03,022
你沒有回復那封…
You never answered the telegram...

1720
02:32:03,257 --> 02:32:06,556
來自第三帝國海軍基地的電報
...from the Admiral of the Navy of the Third Reich.

1721
02:32:06,794 --> 02:32:09,262
據我所知，在奧地利
I was under the impression, Herr Zeller...

1722
02:32:09,530 --> 02:32:13,022
電報的內容是私人的
...that the contents of telegrams in Austria are private!

1723
02:32:13,734 --> 02:32:17,261
最少在我所知的奧地利是如此
At least, the Austria I know.

1724
02:32:18,405 --> 02:32:20,032
我奉命…
I have my orders...

1725
02:32:20,274 --> 02:32:22,435
今晚帶你去基地
...to take you to Bremerhaven tonight...

1726
02:32:22,710 --> 02:32:24,905
接受你的職務
...where you will accept your commission.

1727
02:32:26,046 --> 02:32:31,484
我怕不可能了
I'm afraid that's going to be quite impossible.

1728
02:32:32,086 --> 02:32:33,815
你看…
You see, we...

1729
02:32:34,388 --> 02:32:37,221
我們全家…
...all of us, the entire family, will be...

1730
02:32:38,292 --> 02:32:40,317
今晚要在音樂會上演唱
...singing in the festival tonight.

1731
02:32:40,627 --> 02:32:43,095
事實上我們現在就要去
As a matter of fact, we're going now.

1732
02:32:43,731 --> 02:32:46,598
不可能現在讓他們失望的
We couldn't possibly let them down now.

1733
02:32:46,800 --> 02:32:49,769
-我希望我們不會遲到 -是的
- I just hope we're not too late. - Yes.

1734
02:32:50,003 --> 02:32:52,904
你叫我相信，你艦長…
You ask me to believe that you, Captain von Trapp...

1735
02:32:53,140 --> 02:32:54,607
要去演唱會唱歌？
...are singing in a concert?

1736
02:32:55,008 --> 02:32:59,138
相信我，這會是最棒的表演
Believe me, it will be a performance beyond anything even I've dreamt of.

1737
02:32:59,513 --> 02:33:04,143
吉勒先生，像你一樣 我也是身懷絕技的
Like you, Herr Zeller, I, too, am a man of hidden talents.

1738
02:33:04,852 --> 02:33:06,183
是的
Yes.

1739
02:33:06,453 --> 02:33:08,944
這是節目表
Here, program.

1740
02:33:13,961 --> 02:33:16,293
上面只有孩子的名字
It says only the names of the children.

1741
02:33:16,530 --> 02:33:19,795
上面說范崔普家庭歌詠團
It says the von Trapp Family Singers...

1742
02:33:20,033 --> 02:33:23,093
而我是范崔普家的頭兒 不是嗎？
...and I am the head of the von Trapp family, am I not?

1743
02:33:25,372 --> 02:33:29,172
穿著這些旅行裝？
And these travel clothes that you're all wearing?

1744
02:33:30,010 --> 02:33:31,534
是我們的制服
Our costumes, naturally.

1745
02:33:31,812 --> 02:33:35,213
今晚天氣不好 穿禮服會對孩子的嗓子有影響
This night air is not good for the children's voices.

1746
02:33:41,455 --> 02:33:44,982
稍微延遲執行命令沒什麼大不了
Well, a slight delay in my orders will not be serious.

1747
02:33:46,193 --> 02:33:47,717
你們
Therefore...

1748
02:33:48,562 --> 02:33:50,189
去唱吧
...you will sing.

1749
02:33:51,131 --> 02:33:53,122
你們全部都要唱
You will all sing.

1750
02:33:53,500 --> 02:33:56,025
這正是我希望的
But only because that's what I want.

1751
02:33:56,970 --> 02:34:00,406
這表示奧地利一切都沒有改變
It will demonstrate that nothing in Austria has changed.

1752
02:34:01,141 --> 02:34:03,336
你們唱完後
And when you have finished singing...

1753
02:34:03,644 --> 02:34:06,807
我就要帶艦長到北萊梅港
...you, Captain von Trapp, will be taken to Bremerhaven.

1754
02:34:08,081 --> 02:34:10,811
現在，你們上車吧
Now, if you will all get into your car...

1755
02:34:11,051 --> 02:34:14,885
我們要護送 范崔普家庭歌詠團去演唱會
...we will escort the von Trapp Family Singers to the festival.

1756
02:34:15,756 --> 02:34:17,917
吉勒先生，用不著護送
No escort will be necessary.

1757
